text:
six years ago, i graduated from @iccedu in this exact room, today i returned for a training session on sexual violence prevention. 
those of us in the hospitality, "night life" industry are on the front lines of prevention approach and bystander intervention. 
there are a lot of blurred lines in the industry under the pretense that the customer is always right but at what expense? 
alcohol is the most common drug used to facilitate sexual assault. usually we are the ones providing the alcohol but we can check in on our patrons and make sure they are okay and feel safe. we can't save everyone in all situations but awareness is important. 
there are many telling signs that someone is uncomfortable in a situation. men, women, transgender and non-binary, sexual violence affects us all. 
the world is a better place with you in it 🌍💖 @outsmartnyc did a great job at teaching preventive measures, this training session should be given in all restaurants and bars. 
thank you @womeninhospitalityunited for hosting this session. 
#endvictimblaming #maleprivilege #checkin #compassion #compassionatepartier #sexualharassment #toxicmasculinity #endthestigma #sexualviolenceprevention #domesticviolenceawareness #domesticviolence #culturechange #latinx #almamatter #culinaryschool #cheflife #barlife #hospitality #lgbtq #metoo #lovenotes

text:
21 years ago yesterday i got married.  for all of the wrong reasons.  we weren’t friends, i didn’t feel heard.  or safe. 
and yet after some struggles and a date rape in college he seemed “safe enough”. and i was going to be normal.  no music, no dancing.  a fair amount of alcohol and i would be fine. 
get a job, chop wood and carry water.  it would be fine i kept telling myself.  the thing is i wasn’t fine.  i really thought i was broken and this was as good as it was going to get. 
we were young and getting married seemed like the next logical step.  two years later when i filed for divorce i got a tattoo of mickey mouse from the sorcerers apprentice to remind me that anything was possible.  still, i thought i was broken.  so the men i chose were broken too.  fast forward 17 years of struggling through alcoholism, drugs, relationship addiction...still i thought i was broken.  no matter what shamans i hired, cords i cut, or how many times i watched the secret i still felt broken. 
until i had a coach i trusted and felt safe enough to heal.  and after all of that the healing was actually simple.  simple, but not easy. 
real healing does happen when we have someone in our lives who sees us, sees that what we’re doing in a perfectly understandable response with no judgement. 
only then can we see that the door to the cage was open all along. “i know why the caged bird sings, she has a song”

the door is open, sister.  come out and play 🌈💕

text: i interrupt my posting of work in progress to announce that “blanket statement iv,” the 4th in my series of large knitted framed gender statements, will open at the fuller craft museum’s “context: language, media, and meaning” exhibition tomorrow night. the juror, bruce hoffman, director of gravers lane gallery in philly, also chose my “this is my binder” piece on transgender. these works are passionate statements of love and support for my son. the museum, in brockton ma, will house the show thru feb 24. come see my work and that of many other fiber artists in this show of surface design association artists. #nancymooreart #gender #fiberart #fulkercraftmuseum #transgender #textileart #metoo #surfacedesignassociation #sda #katonahmuseumofart #kmaa

text:
let’s start from the very beginning. this was the first time i ever picked up a paintbrush. i had to leave this painting behind in california when i was running from an abusive boyfriend. i painted this in 2009. i just lost my first baby, and blamed myself a lot due to being severely underweight from an eating disorder. my marriage was falling apart. i was unhappy. as a kid i always drew. doodles mainly. a friend suggested i pick up a brush. this was the first time i felt some form of relief from emotional pain. music also played a big factor, and the two combined started my heart towards a new direction my life would take me. it was scary. it was not the norm, especially growing up southern baptist in texas. it would require me leaving everything i thought i knew, and popping the tiny bubble that others may have made for me, but i kept myself in. i have been toying with how to tell my story, while still healing, and in the process maybe helping even just one other person out there. my goal is to travel the world and let my story show that there is a light at the end. and though i may not have my happy ending yet, i am making it. i’m my own knight in shining armor. and if this is not something you care to read about, or if you were only following me because you thought i was “hot” or i had rad selfies... this may not be for you. i invite you to unfollow now. this is for me, and anyone else who wants to see hope. i watched a video the other day about “social media influencers.” i wish i remember who made it so i could credit him. but he said “if they do not leave your page feeling better than when they came in, what influence are you having in them?” i want you to leave with hope, because i know i need that with the people i choose to follow. i’m still a work in progress. but through all this, i found i am my greatest art piece. i have always been my own artwork. 
also, i know that was cheesy. fucking deal with it. oh, and the f-bombs. ima curse a lot.

text:
the mosaic literary conference will have award-winning novelist #nicoledennisbenn deliver the 2018 keynote.

nicole dennis-benn is the author of the debut novel, #herecomesthesun. dennis-benn is a lambda literary award winner and a recipient of the new york foundation for the arts artist grant, named by time out magazine as an immigrant making a stamp on new york city. her debut novel has received much acclaim including: a new york times notable book of the year, a npr best books of 2016, an amazon, barnes & noble, entertainment weekly, and kirkus reviews best book of 2016, a buzzfeed best literary debuts of 2016, among others.

mosaic literary conference 2018
november 17, 2018, 12pm
the bronx museum of the arts

the year’s conference will explore the current wave of women’s empowerment and how it’s been historically reflected in artistic narrative -literature, media, visual art. they will specifically explore the #metoo movement and how women writers continue to hack at patriarchy.  #literaryconference #mosaicmagazine @mosaicmagazine

today, anmol is a popular instagrammer. she also runs an ngo called acid survivors saahas foundation for others who’ve been scarred. with a positive attitude and a bright smile, she calls herself the ‘happiest girl on earth’. how can someone, scars or not, be this positive all the time, we wonder. but she doesn’t have all the answers. “growing up, i would keenly read inspirational books. maybe that’s how,” says the 23-year-old.

text:
well...i'm finally getting ready to tell this little story of mine. this isn't a new story. this is an old story. this is a story all too familiar to girls and women around the world. this is a story about being young and naive and having someone much older, bigger and stronger decide to take advantage of my innocence. this story changed who i am and shaped a huge portion of my life because i didn't know how to cope with what had happened. 
people ask why victims don't speak up sooner. i didn't tell anyone when this happened. not. a. soul. i carried the blame on my back for years. i didn't fight back. i could have screamed, yelled or tried to run away. i didn't do any of those things because i was scared. i was scared that if i did fight back things might have gotten worse. 
so here's a little clip of my upcoming video. this happened to me when i was 17. i wrote the song when i was 21 and only now am i finally ready to share my story. #metoo #mystory #metoomovement #comingsoon #newmusic #newmusicvideo #newvideo #thatday

text: i have not read this book . . . yet. i am coaching a group of kids for the 2018-2019 oregon battle of the books. george is about about #gender and that's all i know because, like i said, i haven't read it yet. i received an email from someone this morning about not wanting a child to read this book, not wanting a child to participate in the meetings around this book because this child is too young. fine that's an opinion. but i'll tell you this, that may be an opinion, but it's the wrong one to have. i do not believe that any topic should be off limits from any child of any age. i want my kids to feel they can ask me any question they come up with. sure, there are tons and tons of things i don't want to talk to my kids about. i don't want to tell my kids that daddy's penis goes in mommy's vagina, i don't want to tell my sons that murphy is going to bleed once a month and that i do and ej and grady are going to too. i don't want to tell my kids that i have been raped. but you know why i don't want to tell my kids this stuff because it makes me feel uncomfortable. how do i know it makes me feel uncomfortable because i have talked to a few of my kids about this stuff and it was uncomfortable. but it also was awesome, it was informative for everyone, i got questions i couldn't imagine they would come up with and in the end we bonded. so why do i talk about this stuff when i'm mentioning the book george? well, from my very limited research the rates of depression and suicide (to name a few) surrounding gender issues is astronomically high. i'm going to jump out on a limb here and assume some of this is wrapped up in shame. soooooooo if we bring our children into this world (in whatever form you have brought them in) we should let them know right out of the gate they can talk to us about anything and we are going to do the same with them. i do not fear raising my kids, i take it as comes. i have six children i am not naive in believing we are going to skate out of pain, struggles, sadness and hopefully not loss. but goddammit i will not shy away from discussing anything with my chi

text:
i have had the honour of having some excellent female friends in my life over the years and few of them have even trusted me with their harassment / eve-teasing stories — the stories that disturbed and shocked me to my very core. the things, they faced in the hands of some strangers and some of their very own, are indescribable. these incidents never leave these people, and you can tell how much it has affected them just by the way they share their experiences. for my every angry and gutted response, they added, "that's nothing", indicating the actual degree of harassment they have to endure their entire lives, as if it's a part and parcel of being a girl. the saddest part is, most of the times, it happened when they were very young, and they haven't told this to any of their family members till date.

this #metoo movement is doing fantastic things around the globe, but i can understand why it can't flourish in pakistan. unfortunately, in a society that's innately judgmental and full of self-righteous people, it takes much more courage to come forward and speak up. the sense of guilt and shame the victims feel because of this also increases considerably in a closed society like ours. it doesn't mean that the evils of harassment don't exist here as much. this is happening all around us. turning a blind eye to it doesn't change the reality. we shy away from talking about it as if it impurifies us, but the truth is, even according to our religion, we are taking part in this by staying silent.

i sincerely hope that the idea behind the movement extends to our roots and so much so that no girl (or boy) hesitates to confide in their immediate family members if any such thing happens to them. and i also hope that some day we find it in ourselves to openly talk about these matters and stand in harmony against this gut-wrenching disgrace to the society. may allah protect and guide us all.
.
.

text:
the abusive relationship cycle with a narcissist looks like this:
.
phase 1: idealization. victim is immediately swept off their feet, smothered with gifts and attention, and over the top romance. the relationship tends to move quickly (early declarations of love, future planning, etc.) the victim believes they have found their soulmate.
.
what the narcissist is doing in this phase is mirroring, grooming, isolating, and studying the victim. once the victim is bonded to the narcissist, the relationship takes a dive into the next phase.
.
phase 2: devalue. victim begins to see cracks in the narcissist’s mask. when they witness the narcissist participate in unsavory behaviors that are true to the narcissist’s “true self” (ie: veiled humor, lies, envy, arrogance, anger, etc.) and attempts to reign the narcissist in, they are punished through a variety of subtle and insidious forms of emotional and psychological abuse. (ie: gaslighting, withholding affection, silent treatment, insults, etc.)
.
what the narcissist is doing in this phase is conditioning and devaluing. they are training the victim to turn a blind eye to their unhealthy behaviors. idolize and admire the narcissist, put their needs first, validate their delusion of entitlement and superiority, or pay a price.
.
phase 3: discard. confused by their partner’s hot and cold behavior, and worn from the abuse, the victim is at their wits end. the victim may discard/break up with a narcissist at this point. or, the narcissist will do so in a cruel and callous way (ie: cheating, acute abandonment, full detachment, avoidance, silent treatment, assault) as a punishment for not giving the narcissist what they wanted: unrelenting attention, admiration and validation.
.
perpetually bored, mean spirited, and nothing ever being good enough for a narcissist, what they are doing here is showing their true selves.
.
phase 4. hoover. the narcissist comes crawling back to the victim, either pretending nothing happened and the victim was blowing things out of proportion, or professing their love and promising to change. but true change doesn’t happen and the cycle continues. 💛🦋

text:
most of the time the abuser is somehow able to convince the abused that it is ok or normal.  most of the time in cases of child sexual abuse, the child is unable to understand the complexity of the issue. we are still just growing aware of our body. we know the theory, we know what sex is, maybe, but we do not comprehend the meaning in its true sense. it is still very biological for a kid.

consent comes in when differentiating between abuse and harassment. however, in cases of child victims, harassment is always abuse. the child is incapable of rendering his/her true consent, due to non-comprehension of the questions posed.i.e. it is not an informed consent. ‘didn’t say no’ does not mean ‘said yes’. thus every incidence of child sexual harassment amount to sexual abuse, as it is forced, tricked or or result of confusion.
#childsexualabuse
#sexualharassment #metoomovement #metoo #meetooindia #survivor

text:
ride to world's most dangerous roads 👍
.
.
i mostly had confined my riding to city and nearby weekend tours. it was time to undertake something that will put both man and his mean machine to test. hence, i drew an ambitious plan to ride on killar to kishtwar route on my bajaj pulsar rs200. while touring on highways seemed familiar however, riding near cliffhanger in slush required determination and application of skills with focus. all this had to be accomplished when i had met with an accident on day 1 which resulted in a big wound on my left leg.. after careful scrutiny and examinationi decided to  carry on with the excrutiating pain. successful completion of the tour  gave me a sense of pride and a blueprint for future tours. it was indeed #astepbeyond for me.
@xbhp @motulindia @himalayanwanderer_rahul .
.
.

text: recently i had a dream where i walked up a flight of stairs and spirits were getting clearer and clearer as i got higher up, i kept reminding myself not to be afraid that the veil was thin that is why i could see them. once to the top there was a door, i was greeted by a man on the other side of the door. he guided me through this place that i realized was the underworld, where the spirits looked like normal people but they were telling me how long they had been there and the years were back in the early 1,000s. he walked me around this path and i spoke to a bunch of people. until we came back to the door, i said goodbye and stepped back through to the door way. the spirits were there but looked like ghosts again and so were my mother and 2 kids. i reminded them not to be afraid and told my son we have to carve our pumpkins to keep out the negative ones, so he would feel better. then i started riding a ghost up and down the stair way. i now believe the dream was me going on my decent to the underworld just like inanna(venus) aphrodite, the man who greeted me was hades(pluto)anubis. and walking out was my rebirth, and riding the ghost up and down signified my gift for facing my fears and going in was now i get to travel freely between the worlds. this picture i created shows the journey of venus and myself and all of us willing to do the dirty work of shadow integration and death and rebirth. on march 31st 2017 my 30th birthday. venus began her 584 1/2 day cycle as the aries warrior goddess. we can look back and see how this played out on the world stage with all the woman rage and #metoo movement and things like that. she went retrograde in scorpio on oct. 5th to initiate her death and rebirth  journey. today oct. 26th she is being conjuncted by the sun, this is the start of her 5 days in the tomb until oct. 31st where she will be rebirthed as the morning star on nov. 1st. stepping into her libra goddess of justice archetype when she is fully rebirthed on nov. 16th for the next 19 months. bringing balance and peace and justice to the world. which is happening conjunct the divine feminine spica. this feels like the total rebirth of the divine feminine stepping in

text:
this shabbos i will be at the carlebach shul to daven and eat meals with yidden from all walks of life. we unite to celebrate our unconditional acceptance of one another - our fellow human with a pintele yid.
under the surface of this achdus & uplifting unity, i feel rage & sadness on behalf of my sisters who were sexually abused by carlebach. i have read about their emotional traumas & the sexual violations of their bodies: i validate each and every one. it is in these moments of intersection bt awe and disgust towards carlebach’s legacy that strengthen my muscles in an area that i am fascinated with: the grey, the murky, the nuance.
it is easy to use polarizing terms to navigate our confusing environment: evil vs good, political left vs right, male vs female, heterosexuality vs homosexuality, legal vs illegal. i personally like to challenge myself to use empathy to see both sides - to understand that the human condition is fluid, multi-dimensional, layered like an onion.
carlebach’s sexual exploitation of females is abhorrent and unforgivable. but should that strip him of his strengths as a pioneer within the community as an advocate for equality, love, & spiritual enlightenment? if he were alive today, he should stand trial for his abuse of power and publicly accept culpability for his actions, doing whatever he can to repair what he has broken in countless women. but should we completely extinguish the memory of a man who has solidified jewish identity through his music & his philosophies?
my intuition tells me this: do not ignore or deny the allegations - it is your duty to the victims to know their pain & their stories. but you can choose to compartmentalize his offenses in attempt to extract spirituality & joy from the ripple effects of his life work. if his offenses trigger you & disenchant you with religion and spiritual leaders, stay away from his music or his teachings. but most of all, allow space for your neighbor to process carlebach’s legacy in the way that feels natural to him/her, & be flexible with your own changing feelings towards carlebach as you evolve through different phases of your emotional, sexual, and spiritual identity. good shabbos!

text:
"lately, heard has been throwing herself into her humanitarian work and activism. she went to washington d.c. to show her support for survivors on the day supreme court justice brett kavagnaugh was confirmed in october and recently finished up a stretch speaking at the one young world summit in the hague.
“it’s incredibly rewarding to be able to use what experience i’ve lived and endured, suffered, survived through,” she said. “it’s amazing to be able to use one’s experiences in life to help others, to help push the conversation forward, to change the conversation.” when asked if she has felt supported and listened to in the past few years, and in light of the #metoo movement, heard again looked to the future.
“i am very happy that i have moved on with my life and keep moving on with my life,” she said. “i just keep wanting to do with my life that which makes it better for other people and myself. and doing the right thing and moving forward and dedicating yourself to justice, truth, to doing what’s right and helping others when you can — that’s everything to me. that’s all i’m interested in.” " - such a strong and inspiring woman 👏 love you so much @amberheard

.
this makes film festival screening number five!!!
.
check them out at:
www.theindiefest.com
.
take...advantage...of...every...opportunity folks!!
.
stay focused and stay hungry!
.
special shout out to everyone that continues to support my spoken word & filmmaking efforts both new people i've recently befriended on here as well as my other "real ones".
.
have a safe and wonderful weekend everyone!!
.

text:
last monday was the anniversary of the #metoo movement gala  recognizing leaders in this movement with the new york women's foundation at @theplazahotel the evening was filled with some of the most incredible women @taranajaneen @milano_alyssa , dr. mary t. bassett, the co-founders of @levelforward  abigail e. disney, adrienne becker, rachel gould, and angie g. wang and many more along with the ceo of the @nywomensfdn ana oliveira.

thank you @collettevsmith for inviting me as your guest to witness this empowering evening for women! #radicalgenerosity

there is still time to donate for this very worthy cause in support of women at https://www.nywf.org/

donations will go to helping support an organization like 'hot bread kitchen, where women will have the opportunity to be part of paid programs to learn the trade of bread baking and pursue careers in the food manufacturing business.' other organizations such as 'girl be heard, where underserved young women develop and celebrate their voices through socially conscious theater making.' #foodcaster #foodcasternews #foodcastertv #foodcastersquad #thefoodcaster #metoomovement #theplaza #nywomensfdn #radicalgeerosity #womenequality #womensrights #levelforward  #bossbabe  #foodcasterapproved

text:
#francisrenaud #silencebreakers "en attendant sa rencontre bénie avec #oliviermarchal, il essuie les déconvenues. il raconte dans son autobiographie qu'un «superdirecteur» de casting en vue sur la place de paris lui dit clairement que s'il n'accepte pas de «coucher», il n'obtiendra pas de rôle. il en profite pour lui caresser la cuisse de sa «grosse main»: «francis, le droit de cuissage, ça existe. pour réussir, il faut coucher», assène-t-il (p.160). incorruptible, doit dans ses bottes, l'acteur sera «black-listé» plusieurs années.

par la suite, francis renaud ignorera les avances d'#andrétéchiné «perturbé» par son charisme et celles de son assistant (p. 194-195) et se retiendra de frapper #catherinebreillat: elle l'avait poussé à bout en l'obligeant à «jouer» une scène de sexe qui n'était pas prévue dans le scénario de parfait amour (p.2014). «ils savent que je sais... je comprends mieux les suicides de certains acteurs, le milieu ne pardonne pas, il vous écrase, vous méprise...», déplore francis renaud.

par bonheur, il a également fait de belles rencontres. outre olivier marchal qui l'engage dans tous ses polars (gangster, mr73, les lyonnais,...), yves montand qui lui a signé un autographe, jacques demy«disponible», luc besson en train de tourner un clip de mylène farmer devant lequel il perd sa voix, isabelle adjani, gérard depardieu, burt lancaster dans le fantôme de l'opéra, georges lautner ou jeanne moreau (il pousse son fauteuil roulant dans la vieille qui marchait dans la mer)."
.
.

from @metoo_pressreview
• • •
#sexualharassment in #frenchfilmindustry : #francis_renaud #frenchactor #silencebreakers : "en attendant sa rencontre bénie avec #oliviermarchal, il essuie les déconvenues. il raconte dans son autobiographie qu'un «superdirecteur» de casting en vue sur la place de paris lui dit clairement que s'il n'accepte pas de «coucher», il n'obtiendra pas de rôle. il en profite pour lui caresser la cuisse de sa «grosse main»: «francis, le droit de cuissage, ça existe. pour réussir, il faut coucher», assène-t-il (p.160). incorruptible, doit dans ses bottes, l'acteur sera «black-listé» plusieurs années.

par la suite, francis renaud ignorera les avances d'#andrétéchiné «perturbé» par son charisme et celles de son assistant (p. 194-195) et se retiendra de frapper #catherinebreillat: elle l'avait poussé à bout en l'obligeant à «jouer» une scène de sexe qui n'était pas prévue dans le scénario de parfait amour (p.2014). «ils savent que je sais... je comprends mieux les suicides de certains acteurs, le milieu ne pardonne pas, il vous écrase, vous méprise...», déplore francis renaud.

par bonheur, il a également fait de belles rencontres. outre olivier marchal qui l'engage dans tous ses polars (gangster, mr73, les lyonnais,...), yves montand qui lui a signé un autographe, jacques demy «disponible», luc besson en train de tourner un clip de mylène farmer devant lequel il perd sa voix, isabelle adjani, gérard depardieu, burt lancaster dans le fantôme de l'opéra, georges lautner ou jeanne moreau (il pousse son fauteuil roulant dans la vieille qui marchait dans la mer)."
.
.
@francis_renaud
#larageaucoeur #hugoetcie #lefigaro #presse #interview

text:
in 2014 canadian radio talk show host jhian ghomeshi was arrested and charged with a series of sexual assault claims.⁣
⁣
timeline ⁣
⁣
late 2014 accusations brought forward against ghomeshi regarding sexual assault claims and overcoming resistance. ⁣
⁣
cbc and carleton university launch private investigations. carleton concludes no students were ever affected and no complaints of placement.cbc review by janice rubin:management had to have known about the abusive conduct no steps were taken. ⁣
⁣
nov 2014-ghomeshi turns himself in and released on 100,000 bond. also let go by cbc due to accusations.todd spencer executive director of hr fired.⁣
⁣
jan 8 2015 ghomeshi charged with 3 more counts of sexual assault. feb 2016 complainant questioned re;reliability/honesty. complainant sent emails a year after “sexual assault” with bikini pictures and described them as bait to explain why he attacked her. ⁣
⁣
lucy decoutere alleges in court she was slapped without warning and choked until she couldn’t breathe. emails sent hours later by the accuser detail her apparent enjoyment “you kicked my a** last night and that makes me want to f**** your brains out”. ⁣
⁣
a handwritten letter stated “i loved your hands”. she then stated she was trying to please the accused because she blamed herself for the crimes. ⁣
⁣
march 24,2016 the judge acquitted the accused on all charges. the judge stated that inconsistency and deception had weakened the prosecutions case. the job of witnesses was not to just navigate through the case but one thing only. tell the truth, the whole truth and the truth only. ⁣
⁣
what are your thoughts?⁣
⁣
 #rapevictim #metoo #falseclaims #sexualassault

text:
they go low, we #govote. i’m like a mermaid, i #makewaves. blue ones.
.
.
this is a long post. i get emotional when i #vote. always have. i think of my great uncles’s purple heart. my grandad. my dad. people like amy mcgrath in ky. all with so much sacrifice for me to do this simple thing.
.
.so much more important now. these privileges are at risk. 100 years ago i, as a woman, couldn’t vote. now someone is trying to figuratively put their hand over my mouth, like the scotus nominee literally did to dr. ford. our black gubernatorial candidate has had racist robocalls against him as the confederate flag still flies everywhere. this matters. “when they came for me, there was no one left to stand up.” if you’re not affected yet, wait. or better yet, stand up now for those under attack while there’s still time.
.
.there was a line in #lakewoodranch, and there has been all week. in our little bubble. 15 minutes to wait, such a small inconvenience compared to native americans in north dakota or to the disenfranchised in georgia. i would’ve waited all day. thanked every volunteer. i’ll be one of those volunteers next week. .
.everyone had sample ballots in hand. us, too. i’ve never been more aware of national and local politics. and it looks like more people care enough to research beforehand.
.
.my social posts may not convince anyone on anything. but if i can make you consider voting if you’re on the fence, that’s enough.
.
. #vote #pleasevote #bringithome for us @andrewgillum #metoo #womenvote #igers941 #igersflorida #womensmarch #itwasalwaysacape #earlyvoting #lovefl #yeson4 #acluvoter

text:
#predators identified so far -

1. faisal edhi - sexually harassed me; can only imagine what he does with the vulnerable women and children in his care

2. feica - sexually abused children who were friends with and as old as his own children.

3. prof. seher ansari - sexually harassed students and female colleagues; also sexually abused children.

all three are happily being courted by our brogressives, ideology be damned. good work, feels great to know where "our" folks stand.

two of feica's five victims, who had contacted me, have #fibromyalgia - the same thing that i have. these brave people risked flare-ups for this. they wrote to the @dawn_dot_com readers editor. they did everything that they were asked to do, and are now having to deal with emotional and physical pain on their own. and here are folks who can't even be bothered to distance themselves from these predators online, let alone offline. shame.

the government, meanwhile, wants me to bring witnesses from the edhi orphanages who have been sexually abused, in order to initiate an inquiry into faisal edhi's predatory ways. i... i don't have the words. actually, i do, but none of those words is nice. fuck this shit. stop protecting abusers.

#metoo #metoopakistan #edhi #edhifoundation  #pakistan

text:
#metoo - the effectiveness lurking within the hype

following the global outrage over the harvey weinstein incident in the west, where the noted hollywood producer was accused of sexual harassment by over 70 women, the #metoo movement has finally arrived in india, engulfing the political, media, and entertainment industry.
in a patriarchal society where sexual assault victims are still routinely blamed, indian women have taken to social media to share detailed accounts of male entitlement, casual misogyny, sexual harassment and alleged molestation by former bosses and colleagues at work, by saying #metoo.this solidarity is powerful since it is rare to see such a large group of people identifying others suffering as their own, and demanding justice.
however, with great  support, comes great criticism. today, people are in a dilemma over where to locate responsibility for sexual abuse: whether it is a woman’s responsibility to withstand and overcome the misogyny that she encounters, or whether it is the shared responsibility of all of us to eliminate it, so that she never encounters it in the first place.
there is a very thin line between the believers of the movement and the people who have become blind feminazis. the campaign is on the verge of becoming a movement where the actual voices that need to be heard are drowning  because #metoo is at times being used for not so apparent reasons.
moreover, we're acting as hypocrites when we believe in principles of 'innocent until proven guilty' while at the same time, the accused  have already been fired from their jobs, and socially been declared sexual predators by the public and media. 
so, it is hight time to step up for all those women and men who have had to ever go through the painful and misogynistic dark side of the society and for those who have been suffering because of false baseless claims driven by a selfish motive.
name: The Round Table Society, KMC

text:
an open letter to a stand up poet.

dear you,

i had never been to a poetry slam before nor did i know how resonating free verses could be until recently when i witnessed spoken poetry for the first time.

it was a warm summer evening and the weather wasn't the only thing getting the better of me until you took the centre stage and breathed life into the most universal of human emotions which for most parts we refuse to let in or let out as we're constantly keeping our guards up. you spoke about pain, longing, love and hope while bringing words and nature together in a metaphorical harmony, the kind that felt like music which only an artist could create.

i am still awestruck by how effortlessly you made words flow in a rhythm while demanding every emotion to be felt. at times they struck like a lightening bolt, at times they calmed like a cool breeze, in the end they made me let go of things, which for a long time, i'd been bottling within me.

you left the centre stage and yet your words continued to linger. i wish i would've told you that night that if soul had a face, it'd look a lot like your verses.

from,
your new fan
suchi.
.
.
(@fictionbysuchi)
.
.
.

an open letter to a stand up poet.

dear you,

i had never been to a poetry slam before nor did i know how resonating free verses could be until recently when i witnessed spoken poetry for the first time.

it was a warm summer evening and the weather wasn't the only thing getting the better of me until you took the centre stage and breathed life into the most universal of human emotions which for most pas we refuse to let in or let out as we're constantly keeping our guards up. you spoke about pain, longing, love and hope while bringing words and nature together in a metaphorical harmony, the kind that felt like music which only an aist could create.

i am still awestruck by how effolessly you made words flow in a rhythm while demanding every emotion to be felt. at times they struck like a lightening bolt, at times they calmed like a cool breeze, in the end they made me let go of things, which for a long time, i'd been bottling within me.

you left the centre stage and yet your words continued to linger. i wish i would've told you that night that if soul had a face, it'd look a lot like your verses.

from,
your new fan
suchi.

15 ਮਈ ਨੂੰ ਮੈਨੂੰ ਫੇਸਬੁੱਕ 'ਤੇ ਉਹਨਾਂ ਦਾ ਪਹਿਲੀ ਵਾਰ ਮੈਸੇਜ ਆਇਆ ਕਿ ਉਹਨਾਂ ਨੂੰ ਮੈਂ ਚੰਗੀ ਲੱਗਦੀ ਹਾਂ| ਉਹਨਾਂ ਅਨੁਸਾਰ ਮੇਰੀਆਂ ਲਿਖਤਾਂ ਤੇ ਫੇਸਬੁੱਕ ਪੋਸਟਾਂ ਦਾ ਉਹ ਇੰਤਜ਼ਾਰ ਕਰਦੇ ਨੇ ਤੇ ਉਹ ਵੀ ਮੇਰੇ ਵਾਂਗੂੰ ਜਿਉਣਾ ਚਾਹੁੰਦੇ ਨੇ| ਜੀਅ ਨਹੀਂ ਸਕੇ ਪਰ ਮੈਨੂੰ ਵੇਖ ਕੇ ਉਹਨਾਂ ਨੂੰ ਲੱਗਦੈ ਕਿ ਅੱਧਾ ਕੁ ਉਹ ਆਪ ਹੀ ਜੀਅ ਰਹੇ ਨੇ| ਮੈਨੂੰ ਪੜ੍ਹਕੇ ਬੜਾ ਪਿਆਰ ਆਇਆ... ਖ਼ੈਰ ਮੈਂ ਪੜ੍ਹਕੇ ਪਿਆਰ ਭੇਜਿਆ| ਫੇਰ ਲਗਾਤਾਰ ਕਦੇ ਕਦੇ ਗੱਲ ਹੁੰਦੀ ਰਹਿੰਦੀ| ਮੈਂ ਚੈਟ ਨਹੀਂ ਕਰਦੀ ਪਰ ਫੇਰ ਵੀ ਉਹਨਾਂ ਦਾ ਕੋਈ ਸੁਨੇਹਾ ਮੈਂ ਅਣਗੌਲਿਆ ਨਹੀਂ ਕੀਤਾ| ਕਿਉਂਕਿ ਉਹ ਮੈਨੂੰ ਹਮੇਸ਼ਾ ਸੱਚੀ, ਮੋਹ ਦੀ ਭੁੱਖੀ, ਆਪਣੀ ਆਪਣੀ ਜਿਹੀ ਲੱਗਦੀ| ਮੈਂ ਉਹਨਾਂ ਨੂੰ ਭੈਣੇ ਕਹਿ ਕੇ ਬੁਲਾਉਂਦੀ| ਪਿਛਲੇ ਦਿਨੀਂ ਮੈਂ ਕੰਮ ਕਰਨ ਵਾਲੀਆਂ ਔਰਤਾਂ ਦੇ ਹੁੰਦੇ ਸਰੀਰਿਕ ਸ਼ੋਸ਼ਣ ਬਾਰੇ #metoo ਲਹਿਰ ਤਹਿਤ ਇੱਕ ਸਟੇਟਸ ਪਾਇਆ ਤਾਂ ਭੈਣ ਦਾ ਮੈਸੇਜ ਆਇਆ ਕਿ ਜੱਸੀ, ਮੈਂ ਕੁਝ ਦੱਸਣਾ ਚਾਹੁੰਦੀ ਹਾਂ... ਮੈਂ ਹੁੰਗਾਰਾ ਭਰਿਆ ਤਾਂ ਭੈਣ ਨੇ ਕਿਹਾ ਉਹ ਲੰਬੀ ਚਿੱਠੀ ਲਿਖੇਗੀ!

text:
el concepto de sororidad es, en mi opinión, muy problemático. más allá de que yo pueda experimentar tanta solidaridad y compasión por un hombre como por una mujer que sufre, esa palabra está demasiado ligada al vocabulario religioso para que pueda apropiármela”, dijo la crítica de arte.

en su décima edición, celebrada en pleno auge mundial de nuevas reivindicaciones feministas, el festival internacional de literatura de buenos aires (filba) fue inaugurado con una pregunta provocadora: “¿existe la mujer?”. la arrojó al auditorio del malba la escritora francesa catherine millet, una de las críticas del movimiento #metoo originado en estados unidos. la mujer no existe, existen las mujeres, vino a responder millet, quien criticó el concepto de sororidad y volvió a arremeter contra las denuncias públicas por abusos sexuales perpetrados hace años.

compartimos el polémico discurso:

todos los que saben algo de psicoanálisis, que han leído al dr. freud y quizá también al dr. lacan (¡y me parece que son muchos en la argentina!), o quienes tan solo han oído hablar de ellos, habrán entendido a qué alude mi título. la famosa aseveración de jacques lacan “la mujer no existe” significa, por supuesto, que se oponía a la idea de una esencia de la femineidad: las mujeres existen cada una en su singularidad y son irreductibles unas a otras. esta idea se opone a la del “eterno femenino” promovida por el romanticismo, así como a la búsqueda de la mujer ideal a la que se dedicaban algunos de sus contemporáneos surrealistas. pensemos en el mito de la musa en andré breton, por ejemplo.

lacan propone esta idea a comienzos de los años ’70, en pleno período de efervescencia de los movimientos feministas.

hace poco, vimos surgir un nuevo feminismo. y, paradójicamente, este neofeminismo hace renacer un vocabulario viejo: en él aparece mucho,  por ejemplo, la “sororidad”. la sororidad significa la unión necesaria de mujeres entre sí, una solidaridad que se apoyaría en una misma condición. en enero pasado, algunas amigas y yo escribimos una solicitada con el título “las mujeres liberan otra palabra”, para criticar los excesos del movimiento #metoo. cuando se publicó en el diario  le mond
name: Cuarto Poder Salta

en su décima edición, celebrada en pleno auge mundial de nuevas reivindicaciones feministas, el festival internacional de literatura de buenos aires (filba) fue inaugurado con una pregunta provocadora: “¿existe la mujer?”. la arrojó al auditorio del malba la escritora francesa catherine millet, una de las críticas del movimiento  en estados unidos. la mujer no existe, existen las mujeres, vino a responder millet, quien criticó el concepto de sororidad y volvió a arremeter contra las denuncias públicas por abusos sexuales perpetrados hace años.

compaimos el polémico discurso:

todos los que saben algo de psicoanálisis, que han leído al dr. freud y quizá también al dr. lacan (¡y me parece que son muchos en la argentina!), o quienes tan solo han oído hablar de ellos, habrán entendido a qué alude mi título. la famosa aseveración de jacques lacan “la mujer no existe” significa, por supuesto, que se oponía a la idea de una esencia de la femineidad: las mujeres existen cada una en su singularidad y son irreductibles unas a otras. esta idea se opone a la del “eterno femenino” promovida por el romanticismo, así como a la búsqueda de la mujer ideal a la que se dedicaban algunos de sus contemporáneos surrealistas. pensemos en el mito de la musa en andré breton, por ejemplo.

lacan propone esta idea a comienzos de los años ’70, en pleno período de efervescencia de los movimientos feministas.

hace poco, vimos surgir un nuevo feminismo. y, paradójicamente, este neofeminismo hace renacer un vocabulario viejo: en él aparece mucho,  por ejemplo, la “sororidad”. la sororidad significa la unión necesaria de mujeres entre sí, una solidaridad que se apoyaría en una misma condición. en enero pasado, algunas amigas y yo escribimos una solicitada con el título “las mujeres liberan otra palabra”, para criticar los excesos del movimiento  cuando se publicó en el diario  le mond

text:
what is women of the planet?
the purpose of this page is to create a community where local women are celebrated as much as famous women. we will showcase local talent, stories and achievements.
we also want to empower women by sharing inspirational quotes and facts about the rise of global gender equality. finally, we want to motivate women by presenting female scientists, noble prize winners as well as many others, and what it took for them to get recognised. 🌞
as for our goals, if many people get involved, we will develop a website and an online group where women can interact. 🌸
the vision of this community is to purely concentrate on the positives of women and even men who actively support global gender equality.

we would love you to get involved, so please send a photo of yourself or of what represents you (good quality) and a sentence or even a story about what your passions, dreams or achievements are. what brought you to where you are now? 
you can also tag us in any post you feel relevant. 🌿 if you need any guidance please feel free to private message us!
.
.
.

text:
ella, “i have cancer. there, i said it. but i’m not devastated… they keep asking, ‘has it hit you yet?’, ‘are you really still okay?’. and honestly, the answer is still yes. to which my understandably devastated friends and family chime ‘and long may it continue!’, with a worried quiver. despite everyone reassuring me that my feelings are not something to apologise for, and that it’ll hit me in stages, i do feel guilty not being able to grieve with everybody. 💪🏾
it was only upon it hitting me that i was able to come to a conclusion about how i wanted to tell everybody… (i’ve told family first out of respect and have given everyone in my family time to process the initial stages of shock).
but now i want to let everyone know so that when my hair falls out i won’t have to worry about still posting pictures online when i’m lucky enough to have a good day, or good however long. i don’t want people to constantly ask how i am like all we can all think about when looking at me, is my cancer. 
so i’ve decided that if there is a book in all of us, this will be mine. what you are currently reading is the prologue to the story. so please, if you are reading this in real time (23.10.18) don’t message me with loads of questions before at least taking the time, to read this first. 🌿
it’s not that i wouldn’t be grateful for the care and time people took, just i would feel bad if i couldn’t answer everyone and i start chemo today.” 🏆

find the strong ella’s remarkable story at
borderlessbella.wordpress.com/blog/
.
.
.

text:
i do love a cazimi aspect when the sun gives all her revitalising and scorching energy to either venus or mercury and lights them up like a new show on broadway.
now (fri 26th oct) she puts venus retrograde in scorpio right up there with top billing, making front page news.
any personal or private thoughts or processes you might be quietly going through with venus digging into her memory bank of shadow elements are going to get the west end show treatment.
if only this were a play in the theatre, but here in real life, the sun is giving venus rx the un-negotiable power to dramatise these dark issues and its mug shot might end up as front page news a la @topshop peter green, billionaire crook (check him out today).
venus rx in scorpio as cazimi is everything for #metoo and #timesup and its following fall out will be as spectacular as it is necessary.
#venusretrograde #venus #venusinscorpio #petergreen #venusandvesta

text:
sleep&trauma 
trauma may lead to many difficulties regarding sleep. insomnia, bad dreams and daytime fatigue. 
here are some tips you can try when getting ready for bed and thinking about your sleep routines to relax your body: .
have a routine!
.
avoid screen time before bed; try reading a book
.
do not watch the news before bed .
.
avoid drugs/alcohol (they can affect sleep and lead to 
various other problems) .
.
avoid coffee in the afternoon/evenings .
.

text:
trigger warning read at your own risk.

8 years ago today.

i was raped.

it was for the 2nd time in my life.

you would think this day would have some trauma for me. 
and it does.

however, look at that hand. there is no ring on it. that hand represents the fact that 8 years ago today. i took my freedom. 
i left my abuser. i took off the ring he had given me in marriage and began the struggle to freedom.

8 years ago today i chose freedom.

it was not easy. it was awful 
it was painful. 
it was scary.

but i did it. and now the day that brings trauma, also brings some pride and relief that i am not in that situation today.

today i wish you, abundance, freedom, and happiness.

#freedom #freedomfromabuse #blessedtangle #noringisagoodthing #rape #ptsd #metoo #survivor #beautifulday #beautifullife #findthepositive #struggletofreedom #worthit #livingmybestlife #8yearsfree #domesticviolence #domesticabuse #enddomesticabuse

text:
the first time i read ochanya's story, i couldn't stop the tears, and it just brought several memories. the truth is 7 in every 10 grown woman has been a victim of abuse and/or rape as a little girl. and what's worse is, if you find yourself surrounded by mad people who would rather protect their sorry excuse of a marriage rather than call out their abusive husband, son or brothers, then you have no hope of survival. 
_
sometimes i feel the world doesn't favour the girl child. from stories of child abuse, being a victim of rape mostly by people you love and expect to protect you, being a victim of baby factories, daily sexual harassment from walking on the street/going to the market/at work, being kidnapped and used as sex slaves, human trafficking etc. the fact that she is easily a target is disheartening.
_
may ochanya's beautiful soul rest in peace. my prayer goes to every girl and woman that has been a victim and carrying around a soul wrenching scar while acting all strong and indifferent, may god heal you. may he heal the scars and give you joy again. sigh.
_
i truly hope we get to that place where we raise better men, men who treat every girl, lady and woman with utmost love, dignity and respect. i look forward to having many more men in our society who stand up against sexual abusers and rapists, men who hold each other accountable on these things. 
_
most importantly, i hope we do more, i hope when we see another ochanya (because they are all around us) we stand up and fight for her. i hope we do not wait until another one die before we show our strength in unity. i truly hope so! 
_
and for those of you who have girls in your care daily being molested and raped by your husbands, sons, brothers etc and yet you keep mute, may god's judgment begin today upon you and all that you hold dear. may peace depart from your camp until you do the needful. how do you people sleep at night? how? sigh! #ennmaepen #metoo #justiceforochanya #justiceforthegirlchild

text:
boka föreläsning med under kevlaret! 
efter en lyckad vår och en hittills fin höst har ca 3500 personer tagit del av vår föreläsning vadåmachokultur. en stor succé! efter #metoo står klart att många vill ta tag i baksidorna av gamla, dammiga normer och idéer om maskulinitet och dess konsekvenser. alla tycks prata om en mer ansvarsfull manlighet och under kevlaret har tagit plats i debatten i snart tre år.

________________________________________

sen i våras har vi föreläst i grundskolor, gymnasier, för arbetslag såväl som fotbollsklubbar och kyrkor. vi har fått glädjen att göra stopp i både dalarna, skåne, göteborg och stockholm för att inte tala om flera stycken på hemmaplan här i östergötland (exempelvis har vi föreläst för i stort sett hela motala (!) vi kan försäkra att en stor mängd ungdomar (och personal) fått god kunskap om detta problemområde; machokulturen och dess negativa konsekvenser.
något som i förlängningen kan leda till: - förstärkt och mer inkluderande jämställdhetsarbete.
- mer förståelse för unga killars situation.
- ökad närvaro hos och respekt för skolkuratorer.
- tydlig signal för normkreativitet och allas rätt att vara sig själva.
- bättre kunskaper om psykisk ohälsa och hur vi kan motarbeta den. - start på ett längre arbete kring jämställdhet och/eller psykisk hälsa? en ordentlig push för ett fortsatt arbete?

________________________________________

så vad väntar din skola, personalgrupp eller företag på? boka under kevlaret redan till vintern! ❤ ser mer info och referenser på vår hemsida eller maila oss på boka@underkevlaret.se för frågor, önskemål m.m.

www.underkevlaret.se/boka

#underkevlaret #macho #föreläsning #machokulturen #manlighet #psykiskohälsa #metoo

text:
paulina, “having grown up on a farm in a small town of poland, my family owned little.
fortunately, my parents decided to pack and move to england in 2004 to ensure a better future for me. they joined a college and got the qualifications required to get a job. witnessing such hard working ethic pushed me to strive for my dreams and make them proud. 🌌
i am now in my final year of university studying economics and international business and hope to be a leader one day, working on globalising renewable energy. 🌿
my passions include painting, travelling and photography and i’m sure i’ll share that on here at some point!” ☺️ what’s your story? ✨
.
.
.

text:
jag har suttit mitt emot trettio olika kvinnor nu. med nästan alla har jag haft samtal som varat i timmar. jag har inspirerats och vuxit en cm i själ och person med varje kvinna som låtit mig få ta del av det innersta och det ytliga..
.
det här kan vara en smal spaning av mig. men vi måste sluta bete oss som om vi vore fiender. jag är rädd att vi kastar oss med termen ”aktivist” allt för lättvindigt. feminist absolut, det köper jag att man kan vara på samma passiva sätt som jag köper att människor är passiva i sin religion. man tror men handlar inte speciellt mycket. men att kalla sig för feministisk aktivist innebär att man aktivt jobbar för att riva strukturerna som patriarkatet vilar på. att riva ner kvinnor med personlig agenda är raka motsatsen till att jobba aktivt för ett jämställt samhälle..
.
vi är våra barns hopp. vi har makten att förändra här. män kan vila på att vi alltid kommer att glömma deras kollektiva totala svek mot oss som grupp. politiker har haft lika stor tillgång till berättelser under  #metoo men aktivt valt att knappt ta i frågan under valet. lite lyktstolpar runt vasaparken är inte nog..
.
jag skulle kunna köra hela harangen om att visst är det giftigt med kvinnor som springer patriarkala ärenden men fan, vi vet ju alla om det. men för att nå dem, så måste vi ju riva de yttre strukturerna så att de inte har någon att springa ärenden åt?.
.
vi överser så mycket skit från män, rättsystem, vård, arbetsplatser och skolor för att vi inte känner att det lönar sig. medan vi vågar ta fighterna med varandra och för vad? chansen att få skriva en krönika för n24?
.
men det skulle kunna löna sig. kanske skulle vi vara bättre på att överse kvinnors bristande kunskap eller ignorans och istället lägga fokus på det största förtrycket. jag vet vad ni tänker ”man kan hålla två tankar i huvudet samtidigt”. men kan vi verkligen det? kan vi vara arga på varandra och samtidigt hålla varandra i handen när det gäller? för det gäller nu. att vara aktivist innebär att göra avkall på personliga vendettor. jag skulle vilja förslå att vi gör avkall på inbördeskrigen och börjar visa vad vi egentligen är ute efter..
.
trevlig helg

text:
let’s get real. skip it if you are wanting only happy thoughts today!
.
.
.
i consider myself an introvert. i lived alone for years. 
but i hate being alone at night. when i was first a single mom i spent months of sleepless nights. roaming the house. checking all the doors and windows repeatedly. i finally adjusted to it (therapy helped). then the husband came along and i didn’t have to spend my nights alone. which is wonderful until lately when he’s had to be out of town several times and every time it’s a struggle for me. especially when the boy isn’t here either. last night i didn’t fall asleep until after 2am. every sound in the house is an alarm bell. eventually exhaustion will take over and i’ll get a few hours. 
these are the leftovers from a night that’s nearly 20 years ago in my past. 
i decided to share this because i’m sure there are others like me and for a long time i thought i was losing my mind over it. i’ve quit judging myself for this reaction. so if you can relate then hugs to you. .
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
#sleeplessnights #beingalone #fear #metoo #survivor #therapyhelps #lettering #handlettering #nosleep #strugglesoflife #trauma #triggerwarning

text:
oftentimes lately i find myself wondering: "how did this happen? how did i go from an elite job with a high paying salary to being forced out and having to sell all the things that were important to me? how did i go from a confident, self-assured woman to this frightened mouse running for cover? how?" the answer isn't simple, but it can be simplified. #sexualharassment . #stalking . #workplaceviolence . #bullying . that is what started it. what finished it was #badpolicy . #humanresources ineptitude . lack of effective policy enforcement that lets a #toxicworkplace thrive. i never wanted to do this. i never wanted to fight a stalker or a huge corporation in the courtroom. i wanted to do my job. but here i am. was i born to do this? to carry this torch? to help people understand what many #women face in the #workplace ? i don't know. and i can't honestly say that i am unafraid... but i learn how to be more so every day. 
#believesurvivors #metoo #timesup #enough #survivor #inspirationalquotes #joanofarc #sexualassault #ideservetofeelsafeatwork #takethesharkoutofthepool

text:
have you ever felt impatient waiting for results? 🤔i know i have! the reality is that real change takes time. nutrition and fitness become a lifestyle and although the change can take time, with consistency, it will last a life time. 🙌🏻
so is it worth it? absolutely, but it wasn’t my first thought! 😬four years ago i was struggling with energy, i had no idea when it came to food, i was constantly up and down with my moods, and was on medications that i was told i would need for the rest of my life. now, to be clear i do believe that there is a time and place for medicine and if you asked me then if i thought food and fitness could change everything i would have told you that you were either crazy or i was already doing that. 😅 i didn’t expect real progress at all but each day i have become a better me. if this is you just know, i get it! i was you and i am here to help because i was frustrated at one point too. i got you. i am now happy, healthy, fit and medication free!! ❤️❤️❤️🙌🏻 i am committed to helping you be the best you while having fun! let’s do this! 💪🏼💃🏻🍏
.
.
.
.
#healthyliving #nutrition #fitness #accountability #cookbook #freeworkouts #healthyishot #hustleandheart #teamwork #metoo #joinus #kidfriendly #kidsarefree

text:
bannon wanted to use the sorts of aggressive messaging tactics usually reserved for geopolitical conflicts to move the us electorate further to the right, wylie said. he had already directed a series of anti-establishment, conservative documentary films and presided over the far-right website breitbart news, but cambridge analytica would mark another step in his overall ambitions to transform the nation.

with financial backing from hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer, bannon co-founded cambridge analytica in 2013 as the us-branch of strategic communication laboratories (scl) group, a british company that advertises how it has conducted "behavioral change" programs in more than 60 countries.

wylie described cambridge analytica as - steve bannon and robert mercer using a foreign, military contractor ... to use some of the same techniques that the military uses ... on the american electorate.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan and drew griffin
cnn

text:
- bannon got it immediately. he believes in the whole andrew breitbart doctrine that politics is downstream from culture, so to change politics you need to change culture. and fashion trends are a useful proxy for that. trump is like a pair of uggs, or crocs, basically. so how do you get from people thinking ‘ugh. totally ugly’ to the moment when everyone is wearing them? that was the inflection point he was looking for.

is what cambridge analytica does akin to bullying? - i think it’s worse than bullying, christopher wylie says. - because people don’t necessarily know it’s being done to them. at least bullying respects the agency of people because they know. so it’s worse, because if you do not respect the agency of people, anything that you’re doing after that point is not conducive to a democracy. and fundamentally, information warfare is not conducive to democracy.

millions of people’s personal information was stolen and used to target them in ways they wouldn’t have seen, and couldn’t have known about, by a mercenary outfit, cambridge analytica, who, wylie says, “would work for anyone”. who would pitch to russian oil companies. would they subvert elections abroad on behalf of foreign governments?

it occurs to me to ask wylie this one night. - yes.

nato or non-nato? - either. i mean they’re mercenaries. they’ll work for pretty much anyone who pays.

it’s an incredible revelation. it also encapsulates all of the problems of outsourcing – at a global scale, with added cyberweapons. and in the middle of it all are the public – our intimate family connections, our “likes”, our crumbs of personal data, all sucked into a swirling black hole that’s expanding and growing and is now owned by a politically

carole cadwalladr
the guardian

text:
wylie said that bannon's plans began to solidify in 2014, when cambridge analytica consulted various republican campaigns and pacs ahead of the midterm elections. the company began to test and apply its psychographics by using facebook data to model individuals' personality types in order to understand how to influence them.

documents show the john bolton super pac, which promoted candidates supported by recently appointed white house national security adviser john bolton, paid cambridge analytical $454,700 in 2014 for "behavioral microtargeting with psychographic messaging." those services included strategies that broke individual voters into "clusters" based on what messages would resonate with them.

wylie also said the company used focus groups and messaging trials in 2014 to test some of the concepts that became core themes of the trump campaign, such as "drain the swamp" and imagery of walls. "a lot of the narratives of the trump campaign were what we were testing in 2014," wylie said.

he added that bannon directly presided over much of the company's initial research. "everything that we were doing ultimately had to be passed up to bannon for approval," said wylie, who left the company in late 2014.

wylie said bannon would fly to london about once a month for company meetings, and during that time he came to understand bannon's ideology. "he really liked the idea of using a military-style approach to changing people's perceptions," wylie said.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan & drew griffin
cnn

tweet_full:
wylie said that bannon's plans began to solidify in 2014, when cambridge analytica consulted various republican campaigns and pacs ahead of the midterm elections. the company began to test and apply its psychographics by using facebook data to model individuals' personality types in order to understand how to influence them.

documents show the john bolton super pac, which promoted candidates supported by recently appointed white house national security adviser john bolton, paid cambridge analytical $454,700 in 2014 for "behavioral microtargeting with psychographic messaging." those services included strategies that broke individual voters into "clusters" based on what messages would resonate with them.

wylie also said the company used focus groups and messaging trials in 2014 to test some of the concepts that became core themes of the trump campaign, such as "drain the swamp" and imagery of walls. "a lot of the narratives of the trump campaign were what we were testing in 2014," wylie said.

he added that bannon directly presided over much of the company's initial research. "everything that we were doing ultimately had to be passed up to bannon for approval," said wylie, who left the company in late 2014.

wylie said bannon would fly to london about once a month for company meetings, and during that time he came to understand bannon's ideology. "he really liked the idea of using a military-style approach to changing people's perceptions," wylie said.

text:
bannon wanted to use the sorts of aggressive messaging tactics usually reserved for geopolitical conflicts to move the us electorate further to the right, wylie said. he had already directed a series of anti-establishment, conservative documentary films and presided over the far-right website breitbart news, but cambridge analytica would mark another step in his overall ambitions to transform the nation.

with financial backing from hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer, bannon co-founded cambridge analytica in 2013 as the us-branch of strategic communication laboratories (scl) group, a british company that advertises how it has conducted "behavioral change" programs in more than 60 countries.

wylie described cambridge analytica as - steve bannon and robert mercer using a foreign, military contractor ... to use some of the same techniques that the military uses ... on the american electorate.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan and drew griffin
cnn

text:
- bannon got it immediately. he believes in the whole andrew breitbart doctrine that politics is downstream from culture, so to change politics you need to change culture. and fashion trends are a useful proxy for that. trump is like a pair of uggs, or crocs, basically. so how do you get from people thinking ‘ugh. totally ugly’ to the moment when everyone is wearing them? that was the inflection point he was looking for.

is what cambridge analytica does akin to bullying? - i think it’s worse than bullying, christopher wylie says. - because people don’t necessarily know it’s being done to them. at least bullying respects the agency of people because they know. so it’s worse, because if you do not respect the agency of people, anything that you’re doing after that point is not conducive to a democracy. and fundamentally, information warfare is not conducive to democracy.

millions of people’s personal information was stolen and used to target them in ways they wouldn’t have seen, and couldn’t have known about, by a mercenary outfit, cambridge analytica, who, wylie says, “would work for anyone”. who would pitch to russian oil companies. would they subvert elections abroad on behalf of foreign governments?

it occurs to me to ask wylie this one night. - yes.

nato or non-nato? - either. i mean they’re mercenaries. they’ll work for pretty much anyone who pays.

it’s an incredible revelation. it also encapsulates all of the problems of outsourcing – at a global scale, with added cyberweapons. and in the middle of it all are the public – our intimate family connections, our “likes”, our crumbs of personal data, all sucked into a swirling black hole that’s expanding and growing and is now owned by a politically motivated billionaire.

carole cadwalladr
the guardian

text:
wylie said that bannon's plans began to solidify in 2014, when cambridge analytica consulted various republican campaigns and pacs ahead of the midterm elections. the company began to test and apply its psychographics by using facebook data to model individuals' personality types in order to understand how to influence them.

documents show the john bolton super pac, which promoted candidates supported by recently appointed white house national security adviser john bolton, paid cambridge analytical $454,700 in 2014 for "behavioral microtargeting with psychographic messaging." those services included strategies that broke individual voters into "clusters" based on what messages would resonate with them.

wylie also said the company used focus groups and messaging trials in 2014 to test some of the concepts that became core themes of the trump campaign, such as "drain the swamp" and imagery of walls. "a lot of the narratives of the trump campaign were what we were testing in 2014," wylie said.

he added that bannon directly presided over much of the company's initial research. "everything that we were doing ultimately had to be passed up to bannon for approval," said wylie, who left the company in late 2014.

wylie said bannon would fly to london about once a month for company meetings, and during that time he came to understand bannon's ideology. "he really liked the idea of using a military-style approach to changing people's perceptions," wylie said.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan & drew griffin
cnn

text:
i am a woman. i am strong because i have had to be. i am kind, resilient, adaptive and i pursue my own path. i will also tell you what i am not. i am not a victim. i am not a billboard on which you can project your own insecurities, i am not clay that you can mold into the shape you desire. i am not here for your amusement. this wasn’t going to be a #metoo post, but i feel like it needs to be. 
________________________
lately, in real life and via social media, i have had some negative experiences. the other day, when i was out walking, minding my own business with headphones in, a man stopped his car in the middle of the road and started yelling and catcalling at me. the fear that surged up in me made me feel disgusted. why should i feel fear for doing something normal? another thing that happened was on my blog, when a creepy older guy commented on a post of mine about my halloween costume, saying it “didn’t show enough skin”.🙄
______________________
i was raised to be a “good girl”. good girls are quiet. they behave. they smile, even when they don’t feel like it. but if that’s what a “good girl” is, than i am not one any more. i am loud, whether i choose to be so through actions, words or silence. i behave in the manner i see fit. i smile when i want to smile, not because a man tells me i would be so much prettier if i would. and i dress the way i want to and don’t need anyone’s approval, commentary, or insights on my appearance or my body.✌🏻
_________________________
when i say #metoo, it is not a cry for attention, it is an acknowledgment of things that have unfortunately happened to me. sexual and emotional abuse from a previous relationship i was in 9 years ago, and instances like the ones mentioned above. i share so that others won’t feel alone.
_______________________
ladies and men, do not be quiet because others can’t handle the truth. the truth is uncomfortable and it’s our job to speak it.

text:
🎃 #ハロウィン deけんぽうカフェ🎃無事終了いたしました。

本日は
①#metoo イベントの報告
②テーマの24条に合わせた最新ニュース
③そして、24条と合わせて今度新しく変わろうとしている
#憲法 草案がどこがどう変わるのか？
細かくチェックしていきました。 ◉24条 現行憲法の口語訳(武蔵野市 子どもとおとなの日本国憲法より)
●家族生活における個人の尊厳と両性の平等として
『結婚は本人同士の考えできめる。また、家族生活に関係のある、さまざまなことにおいて、法律をつくるばあいには、いつでも、家族のなかの一人ひとりがたいせつであること、男女が平等であることを忘れないようにしなければならない』

自民党 憲法改正草案では、
●家族、婚姻などに関する基本原則として
新しく以下が加わります。
『家族は社会の自然かつ基礎的な単位として、尊重される。家族は互いに助け合わなせればいけない』
また、他にも
家族は、扶養、後見、親族などの言葉が付加されています。

この違いは？？
・ 1人1人を大切に→家族単位で助けあう義務
・家族が助けあえず貧しい場合、国の補助が得られにくくなる
・家族という単位を尊重→夫婦別姓認めない、非嫡出子や、離婚した子供の相続権を認めない、離婚がしにくくなる。

そして忘れちゃいけないっっ💦
#98条  新設‼️
🔥緊急事態の宣言😱😱
政府に全権をゆだねることになる😱
指示に従わなければ拷問もあり得る😱
これはテーマに関係なくどういったことなのか
今後も取り上げる予定です。

そして、最新ニュースは
フィフクロhp http://fifcro.space/ にまとめてますよ❤️
みてみてくださいね。

④ #憲法ビンゴ ！ビンゴ景品ハロウィンお菓子❤️
今日出たのは
#97条 #12条 #27条 #9条 #11条 #21条 #13条

日々の生活と関係あることが多くて話も多岐に渡りました。自民党草案とも比べつつ意見交換しました。 ・水道民営化法案、衆院通過。被災地で水道が民営になってたせいで水出なかった話聞いたけどどうなっちゃうの？？
・外国人労働者の賃金は？その前に日本人も労働条件そろってないよね？
・派遣会社に勤めてる人の待遇は？
・そもそも、憲法って権力者が暴走しないために定められたものなんだよね。
・13条も97条も #基本的人権 をこれでもかって載せててびっくりした。侵すことのできない永久の権利💓

さて、
次回の #けんぽうカフェ は
🎅クリスマスdeけんぽうカフェ🤶🎄
来月は第4金曜が祝日なため日にちを変更する予定です。
また、告知いたします。

this was the whole reason for “innocent until proven guilty.” and i say “was,” because these days we are repeatedly circumventing due process and allowing the mob to act as prosecutor, judge, and jury. it’s a deplorable lapse in justice which shows just how far along we already are in terms of societal collapse.

for those who scoff at this statement of fact: check the national registry of exonerations and note how many people have been convicted and imprisoned wrongly on an allegation, without evidence. 
edit: fyi, instagram is censoring my hashtags. i used a few below but could not use my regular anti-feminism hashtags— neither here nor in comments— and can’t figure out which ones ig has a problem with. you can help fight this problem by sharing this info anyway, and posts like these, whether in your stories or elsewhere. thank you! 🙂

text:
it is disheartening how the kannada industry is dealing with the #metoo movement. 
and there also some facebook pages that post pictures of the woman who started the movement saying, "say whatever you wanna say to her, she's the one who started all this!" first off, you don't disown your own people. and the women who are standing up against a  person or celebrity are people who live and work in the same place. 
second off, if you're not directly involved in the issue or the case, unless you wanna support or testify.. you have no role to play in the movement.. please shove your opinions where no one cares! 
thirdly, act responsibly when you own a level of popularity.. be it a page or a social media profile or a blog.. even if you can't spread positivity.. do not spread negativity. the woman who started the movement must have had to take a lot of courage to do it.. and your mockery is disrespectful. 
and lastly.. buzz off and let people be. don't annoy them some more when they're already probably going through a lot. just cos they had the courage to speak out, doesn't mean they have the strength to deal with the nonsense you throw at them. - harini madhusudan 
shameful to see such posts..if u people can't respect a woman... then shut the f.. up and mind ur business... anyways u guys don't respect your mother , sister, daughter and wife...hence creating such posts and posting them..

text:
⭐️⭐️⭐️
a very timely thriller about two women’s quest for revenge on the men who have assaulted or wronged them. while i am all for female empowerment, this one missed the mark for me. i felt like it was such an important topic with the #metoo movement, but i had a very hard time connecting with the characters. i actually guessed the twist about 40% in. i didn’t love it, but i also didn’t hate it; it was just ok for me.
thanks to amy gentry, houghton mifflin harcourt and netgalley for an advanced copy in exchange for an honest review.
📚

#arctober2018 day 26: yellow arc (there’s yellow in the cover 😂)

text:
in order to be pretty and perfect,  is to not say too much, think too much, or vocalize too much. women must not acknowledge that they are able to be independent nor their strength. women are potrayed and must live as a weak, fragile thing. their voices are neither credible or can be held accountable. at least that's what most of the women had been told either directly or not. it is always the women's fault. if she is harrassed, it was her fault and he still have a big career ahead. what most people forgot is, women are not to be kept at home. women aren't less. women also have a big career/future ahead. the power, the truth, the stories are real. so it is time to start appreciating and value each and everyone's opinion, words, stories. 
#art #ideafest #metoo

text:
jumat (26/10), uwrf 2018 kembali menyuguhkan serangkaian kegiatan yang menyentuh hampir semua elemen. mulai dari sejarah, sastra, social movement, hingga ilustrasi. semuanya dibahas oleh para pembicara yang udah nggak perlu diragukan lagi deh track record-nya.

kami mengikuti main program "twenty years later" yang membahas tentang perjalanan reformasi indonesia yang sudah berjalan 20 tahun.

p! juga mengikuti main program "island of inspiration". lanjut nih ke sesi "worth a thousand words" di taman baca di mana para pembicara pada sesi ini merupakan seorang ilustrator dan mereka menceritakan tentang bagaimana ilustrasi mereka menjadi buku dan berbicara layaknya buku pada umumnya meski minim dengan kata.

p! juga ikutan talkshow bertemakan #metoo" di neka museum. talkshow ini membahas soal hashtag yang rame di media sosial yang juga jadi sebuah gerakan di seluruh dunia terkait isu pelecehan seksual dan bagaimana perbedaan yang terjadi di setiap negara.

sorenya, kami mengikuti workshop bertemakan "clear and compelling" yang diadakan di taksu spa & restaurant. workshop ini dipandu oleh mark lynas. 
sore di indus restaurant pun berlangsung main program "cosmopolitan creativity" yang ngebahas tentang bagaimana pindah dari satu wilayah ke wilayah lain dapat mempengaruhi cara kerja penulis.

balik lagi ke neka museum, kami mengikuti main program dengan tema "in praise of slow". tema ini membahas tentang irisan antara slow-life dan produktivitas seorang penulis.

habis gitu, kami santai sejenak dengan menonton film "love is a bird" dari richard oh di betelnut. 
dan terakhir p! mampir ke bar luna dalam kegiatan festival club. kegiatan yang kami ikuti berjudul "the epic" bersama bruce carpenter dan alex vermuelen.

nahh itu dia kegiatan yang kami ikuti di hari keduanya ubud writers and readers festival 2018. masih ada hari ketiga dan keempat nih. tunggu catatan kami soal keseruannya ya?!
#provokemagazine
#provokeuwrf2018 
#uwrf18
name: Provoke! Magazine
tweet_full:
jumat (26/10), uwrf 2018 kembali menyuguhkan serangkaian kegiatan yang menyentuh hampir semua elemen. mulai dari sejarah, sastra, social movement, hingga ilustrasi. semuanya dibahas oleh para pembicara yang udah nggak perlu diragukan lagi deh track record-nya.

kami mengikuti main program "twenty years later" yang membahas tentang perjala reformasi indonesia yang sudah berjalan 20 tahun.

p! juga mengikuti main program "island of inspiration". lanjut nih ke sesi "worth a thousand words" di taman baca di mana para pembicara pada sesi ini merupakan seorang ilustrator dan mereka menceritakan tentang bagaimana ilustrasi mereka menjadi buku dan berbicara layaknya buku pada umumnya meski minim dengan kata.

p! juga ikutan talkshow bertemakan #metoo" di neka museum. talkshow ini membahas soal hashtag yang rame di media sosial yang juga jadi sebuah gerakan di seluruh dunia terkait isu pelecehan seksual dan bagaimana perbedaan yang terjadi di setiap negara.

sorenya, kami mengikuti workshop bertemakan "clear and compelling" yang diadakan di taksu spa & restaurant. workshop ini dipandu oleh mark lynas. 
sore di indus restaurant pun berlangsung main program "cosmopolitan creativity" yang ngebahas tentang bagaimana pindah dari satu wilayah ke wilayah lain dapat mempengaruhi cara kerja penulis.

balik lagi ke neka museum, kami mengikuti main program dengan tema "in praise of slow". tema ini membahas tentang irisan antara slow-life dan produktivitas seorang penulis.

habis gitu, kami santai sejenak dengan menonton film "love is a bird" dari richard oh di betelnut. 
dan terakhir p! mampir ke bar luna dalam kegiatan festival club. kegiatan yang kami ikuti berjudul "the epic" bersama bruce carpenter dan alex vermuelen.

nahh itu dia kegiatan yang kami ikuti di hari keduanya ubud writers and readers festival 2018. masih ada hari ketiga dan keempat nih. tunggu catatan kami soal keseruannya ya?!
#provokemagazine
#provokeuwrf2018 
#uwrf18

text:
quando eu desisto de querer alguma coisa, quando eu abro mão de um desejo.... é aí que a manifestação do que eu realmente preciso,  acontece. 🚫 querer demais alguma coisa é acreditar na percepção de que algo está faltando. 🎯 essa é a ilusão que precisa ser transcendida. 💣 porque a falta, a carência, o obstáculo, não existem, não são reais. mas, sim, parecem reais, somente porque eu ainda estou manifestando essa realidade da carência. 💗 'eu sou a presença de deus que preenche de luz essa situação.' 🎯 - mantra poderoso para manifestar a luz onde eu acredito existir uma ausência. 👣💗 ... #psicomatriz .
.
.
📷 @thedizzyviper

text:
i illustrated this almost 2 years ago, when i was just beginning to try and understand my own trauma and the reactions i had to it. it's been really helpful in my own recovery to learn how the brain functions to keep us alive and safe.⠀
.⠀
when we are under threat, we typically respond with the fight or flight response. we fight back, or we run. but have you ever wondered what happens when you can't fight back or flee the situation? the freeze response kicks in. details in the illustration above, or broken wayyy down: basically, parts of the brain shut down, other parts try to take on those jobs, things get frantic and memories get stored incorrectly. #believesurvivors ⠀

text:
ahoy there 'ziners!⠀
⠀
in this week's podzine, the team put their marching boots on - again - to join the 700,000 or so crowd at saturday's @peoples_vote march in #london. as well as drawing serious props for their signage and indeed dog-age, the team caught up with mps #annasoubry, #sarahwollaston and @joannacherrymp; @lara_spirit of @our_future_our_choice; @sorchaporch92 of the #highlandsandislandsstudentsassociation; standard issue stalwart #janebostock; and #deliasmith. you heard.⠀
⠀
they also chatted to seyi newell from @rosaforwomen, the uk fund for women and girls, about how charities and projects set up to help women can get their hands on some cold hard cash. by way of their #justiceandequalityfund; and #sarahmorgan, host of podcast #thefear drops by to talk about getting the willies in the run-up to hallowe'en. hannah is swiping left on battery bullies in sotw, @jennoff is pondering the ioc's moral compass in jotb, and dunleavy does #disney does #thegooddinosaur, the title of which may or may not be misleading.⠀
⠀
treat your ears!⠀
⠀
#standardissuepodcast #feminism #comedy #currentaffairs #ukpolitics #brexit #halloween #horrorfilms #nowsthetime #metoo #timesup

text: for nearly a month now,  i've been aware of accusations against one of the major figures of the alternative literature (alt lit) movement, a figure and moment i've admired. apparently, said person has been accused of using the movement as a front to sway underage girls in the direction of unwarranted sexual advances. to say this is disturbing is beyond a gross understatement. clearly, my most rueful sentiments are for every person who was a victim of this, and, perhaps, if justice is still a thing, alt lit can be taken in a more positive direction. the following link  is an article of an account by one the people who claimed to have been touched by this. let me know your thoughts. link: http//www.thedailybeast.com/the-star-feminist-author-accused-of-preying-on-underage-girls  #poetry #poetrycommunity #altlit #sexualassault #metoo #teens #poetryofinsta #poetrylover #scandal #poetryisnotdead #writingprompts #poetrycommunityofinstagram #igpoetry
