text:
read this :
i don't usually throw around "piece signs". it's not really my thing, you can probably tell by my face, but the dude taking the photo asked me to do it, and he was my "boss" for this event, so i did.

here's the lesson -
i once taught a horrendous workshop in st. louis. i'm not being dramatic, it was one of the worst experiences in my adult life. i drove 6 hours to have my first class be a private with an older man who had only signed up for it because "i saw your backbend photo and was hoping you'd wear the bra you had on in it." that's what he opened our 2.5 hour private class with. he repetitively asked me to take off my shirt so he could learn better, asked me to scratch my plan (which he wasn't even trying to pay attention to) and only do partner stretches, asked me why he wasn't attractive enough to land a woman, asked why my husband could have someone like me but he couldn't, asked me where i was staying, asked me to stay with him, asked to feel my "young" abs, asked why i wouldn't touch him more, asked me why i was still trying to teach instead of "connect with him" and much more. he asked all these over and over for the next 2.5 hours. i didn't play into any of it and stayed as professional as i could because he had paid a lot, it was my job and i felt like if i didn't finish what i came there to do, i wasn't doing my job. i was holding back tears and absolute fear for hours. when i left he followed me for awhile towards my hotel where i ran inside, pleaded to the front desk man to never tell anyone i was there and cried in my room for the next 6 hours 300 miles away from my family. 
i've had much worse happen to me, but for a grown ass man, 50ish, to force himself on me, physically and mentally, in my safe space was the absolute worst. i didn't agree to teach workshops or teach in general for a few months after that. 
the lesson is - just because someone asks you to do something, even for your job, you don't have to do shit. do not do it if it feels wrong. who fucking cares if a few people get mad or feel uncomfortable for you saying no or walking out - just don't do it if you don't want to.
if it's not a full body yes, it's a no!
name: Jordi Doughty

text:
alfombra roja de los latin amas viste de color a la hispanidad. los vestidos coloridos y los trajes con gráficos y dibujos inundaron la alfombra roja de los latin #amas: latin american music awards en su cuarta edición. la pasarela dejó un claro mensaje sobre el importante aporte de los #hispanos y las mujeres a la sociedad estadounidense.

la mexicana #gloriatrevi destacó a su llegada al teatro dolby, situado en el corazón de hollywood, los ángeles, con un vestido lleno de plumas que defendió a capa y espada. “las mujeres deben vestirse como quieran sin estar pensando en su edad o su peso, no deben dudar en defender lo que quieran porque ahí está su fuerza”, manifestó trevi. 
la cantante #beckyg, por su parte, escogió un vestido con transparencias negro, un color asociado en hollywood al movimiento #metoo.

activismo explícito y corpóreo.

los mensajes también llegaron escritos. rompiendo con el glamur de estos eventos, la actriz #analorenasánchez optó por una camiseta blanca con la frase, en inglés, “no hay límites que las mujeres no puedan sobrepasar”. pero no solo las estrellas traían un mensaje claro. a la gala llegó la “soñadora” astrid silva, una inmigrante indocumentada amparada por el programa de acción diferida para los llegados en la infancia (daca). ella llevaba un vestido azul de gala con un llamado en defensa de los “soñadores” pintado en su falda.

los hombres no se quedaron atrás en las reivindicaciones. el músico puertorriqueño elvis crespo vistió un traje amarillo con aves y arboles dibujados en el pantalón y la chaqueta, que aseguró simbolizaba el colorido que los inmigrantes representan en #estadosunidos.

el cantante venezolano #nacho, nominado a uno de los premios, lució una chaqueta versace llena de símbolos. el intérprete afirmó que los premios latin amas demuestran que los hispanos están al nivel de los artistas estadounidenses

la neoyorquina #lesliegrace vistió un traje largo, también lleno de mensajes que hablaban de poder, coraje y los derechos de la mujer. “vamos a celebrar lo que somos: mujeres, hispanos, inmigrantes y debemos sentirnos orgullosos de eso”, manifestó.

text:
立即 follow @businessfocus.presslogic 【谷歌性侵案】谷歌ceo認解僱48名涉性侵員工，安卓之父魯賓原來也因性侵離職？⠀
·⠀
「我天生脾氣暴躁，不好惹，誰要是再唧唧歪歪，我有的是法子對付他。」連古裝劇《延禧攻略》都走女人敢怒敢發聲路線，間接呼應近十年來的女權意識抬頭。既2017年外媒《紐約時報》深入報道荷里活影業大亨韋恩斯坦（harvey weinstein）性侵等醜聞後，掀起了全球女性me too運動。⠀
·⠀
google一直給人正面、積極、陽光的公司文化，成為了矽谷甚至全球科技公司的範本。然而，在me too運動蔓延到google時，卻勾出了公司不想為人所知的一面。⠀
·⠀
安卓（android）之父-安迪·魯賓（andy rubin）創辦的安卓公司在2005年被google收購後，魯賓便擔任高級副總裁職位，一直負責安卓業務，直到2013年，google突然將魯賓調離安卓部門，魯賓在隔年更默默離開google，當時在矽谷引起多方揣測其離職原因。⠀
·⠀
原來，魯賓涉入性侵行為，有內部員工也證實此事。當時有一位女員工向公司投訴，已婚的魯賓與她除了保持婚外性關係外，更曾在2013年時強迫女方替自己口交，google在調查後也認同了該女員工的投訴。在證據確鑿下，當時的google ceo，也是聯合創始人拉里·佩奇（larry page）雖要求魯賓離職，但並沒有直接將其開除，而是選擇感謝魯賓貢獻的方式，大禮歡送，試圖讓性醜聞壓制下來。除此之外，2014-2018年期間，google每月還會支付魯賓200萬美元，一共9,000萬美元的遣散費，甚至還投資了魯賓離職後所創辦的風投基金playground ventures，完全掩人耳目。⠀
⠀
·⠀
當然，魯賓並不是唯一一位google涉嫌性侵的高管。google現任ceo桑達爾·皮查伊（sundar pichai）25日向員工發送內部郵件指，過去兩年間，google已經解雇了48名涉嫌性騷擾的員工，而當中至少有13名高級經理以上的中高層人員，且都沒有提供任何解僱補貼等。⠀
·⠀
皮查伊在2015年上任後便注重解決性騷擾方面的問題，而此封信件主要是就《紐約時報》之前對其公司報道的性侵風雲作回應，不過其回應只提及在他上任後，公司處理態度，沒有具體提及魯賓一事。⠀
·⠀

tweet_full:
立即 follow @businessfocus.presslogic 【谷歌性侵案】谷歌ceo認解僱48名涉性侵員工，安卓之父魯賓原來也因性侵離職？⠀
·⠀
「我天生脾氣暴躁，不好惹，誰要是再唧唧歪歪，我有的是法子對付他。」連古裝劇《延禧攻略》都走女人敢怒敢發聲路線，間接呼應近十年來的女權意識抬頭。既2017年外媒《紐約時報》深入報道荷里活影業大亨韋恩斯坦（harvey weinstein）性侵等醜聞後，掀起了全球女性me too運動。⠀
·⠀
google一直給人正面、積極、陽光的公司文化，成為了矽谷甚至全球科技公司的範本。然而，在me too運動蔓延到google時，卻勾出了公司不想為人所知的一面。⠀
·⠀
安卓（android）之父-安迪·魯賓（andy rubin）創辦的安卓公司在2005年被google收購後，魯賓便擔任高級副總裁職位，一直負責安卓業務，直到2013年，google突然將魯賓調離安卓部門，魯賓在隔年更默默離開google，當時在矽谷引起多方揣測其離職原因。⠀
·⠀
原來，魯賓涉入性侵行為，有內部員工也證實此事。當時有一位女員工向公司投訴，已婚的魯賓與她除了保持婚外性關係外，更曾在2013年時強迫女方替自己口交，google在調查後也認同了該女員工的投訴。在證據確鑿下，當時的google ceo，也是聯合創始人拉里·佩奇（larry page）雖要求魯賓離職，但並沒有直接將其開除，而是選擇感謝魯賓貢獻的方式，大禮歡送，試圖讓性醜聞壓制下來。除此之外，2014-2018年期間，google每月還會支付魯賓200萬美元，一共9,000萬美元的遣散費，甚至還投資了魯賓離職後所創辦的風投基金playground ventures，完全掩人耳目。⠀
⠀
·⠀
當然，魯賓並不是唯一一位google涉嫌性侵的高管。google現任ceo桑達爾·皮查伊（sundar pichai）25日向員工發送內部郵件指，過去兩年間，google已經解雇了48名涉嫌性騷擾的員工，而當中至少有13名高級經理以上的中高層人員，且都沒有提供任何解僱補貼等。⠀
·⠀
皮查伊在2015年上任後便注重解決性騷擾方面的問題，而此封信件主要是就《紐約時報》之前對其公司報道的性侵風雲作回應，不過其回應只提及在他上任後，公司處理態度，沒有具體提及魯賓一事。⠀
·⠀

text:
#metoo 
i've openly shared my experience with verbal abuse in grade school. but i've been silent about the emotional, financial, mental, physical, and sexual abuse i've faced in my intimate relationships as an adult.

dating, relationships, and sexuality are beautiful, but for myself and many others, it's been a road of heartbreak, lessons, mistakes, and trauma.

it's time that men and the lgbtq community also speak out about their mistreatment, on their own terms of course. 
let's create a new culture where we can confidently and effectively assert boundaries, consent and negotiation.

text:
disclaimer: feminism ahead, keep your patriarchal eyes away from it...
. ||निवेदन||
.
 आपको गुज़ारिश है के मुझे "माँ-बहन" की नज़र से ना देखे,
में अपने भाई-बहन की बहन हूँ,
अपने माता-पिता की बेटी हूँ,
और बस अपने बालक की माँ हूँ,
में आपकी माँ, आपकी बहन नहीं हूँ,
तो आप मुझे बक्श दीजिये उस नज़र से,
क्युकी
जिस समाज को 
अपने लड़को को,
"किसीको बिना वजह अपमान निगाहो से ना घूरो"
जैसी सामान्य बात को,
"सब लडकियों को माँ-बहन की नज़र से देखो"
कहके सिखाना पड़ता हो,
जिस समाज को,
अपनी लड़कीओ को,
करेक्शन "अपनी बहनो" को,
"ये कैसे कपडे पहने है तुमने,तुम्हारा भाई है घर में" कहके ढंकना पड़ता हो,
जो समाज 
किसी लड़की को सम्मान,
"क्युकी असम्मान गलत है तो गलत है"
के कारण नहीं,
परन्तु "अपने घर में भी माँ है, बहन है!" अगर उनके साथ किसीने ऐसा किया हो तो..!"
के डर से देता हो,
उस "नारी-पूजक" "देवी-पूजक" समाज की "माँ-बहन" समजो" नज़र नहीं चाहिए मुझे,
मेरे इस अवास्विकार से परेशान आपको,
माँ-बहन की गालिया देनी हो मुझे तो,
यहाँ "में में हूँ!",
एक सामान्य इंसान,
जिसके कुछ सहज प्रश्न है,
और जिसके पास कुछ साहजिक उत्तर है,
"सामान्य रूप से जिसको आप "मुँह-फट लड़की" के नाम से जानते है" -zarana

we just had to #repost @girltribegang - they’re giving us that #fridayfeeling! 💃🏻 come and see @journalistaltd founder and ceo, holly sutton @wilderride, give her talk on how to #defythedefaults at #gtglive18 on sat 3rd nov in manchester 💪
___

get ⚡️empowered at #gtglive18 and learn how to ‘reject the defaults’. #metoo has shown us that the old patriarchic tropes of 'put up and shut up' need exist no longer. 
_
but what other 'default' positions are sneaking about unchallenged in our personal and business lives? this is what holly @wilderride founder and ceo of @journalistaltd is going to be talking about with a 💥powerhour at our #gtglive18 on 3rd november. 
_
holly says, “we are a business on a mission to make complex issues clearer in health, tech and research through work that works for everyone. we sell ideas, energy and connectivity all of which are hampered by the defaults of long-hours, city centric working and work-life divide. so we choose to put ‘talent’ first and think: how can we attract and grow it? rather than trap and frustrate it. for us, this means flexibility, work-life blend and values based ways of working.

_
as ceo i focus on building modern, outcome focussed ways of working that enable our talent first pr agency to evidence that this way of working is not only best for people, but best for business.“ we'd love you to join us and holly. 
_
link to tickets in our bio 👆grab your friends, plan a road trip 🚘🚘🚘and come and get inspired, get empowered, get connected, get balance and get some me time. 📸 @ishouldb.

text:
so, it's #worldmentalhealthday . so i thought i'd tell yous a bit about mine. it's a bit grim, so if you're not looking for that right now, here's a picture of some badges i got off tod market today.
.
.
.
i've had some pretty major mental health problems since i was 14. psychosis, voice hearing, depression, anxiety, ptsd addiction. all that fun stuff. it's tough. it's tough knowing that it's not going to just go away any time soon. in a lot of ways, this is just how i'm wired now. 
a lot of the time i see the up side to being as i am. having had the life i have makes me pretty accepting of others, i have a lot of insight that others who haven't had my struggles miss. i'm good in a mental health crisis. over all, i have a fire in me that makes me a warm, loving and accepting person for people having hard times to take comfort from. but the fire that makes me so warm has burned my life down more than once. i'm good at rebuilding, and also pretty good at apologies.

a part of how i ended up the way i am is that i was groomed for sexual abuse when i was 13. by a white, middle class man who worked in a shop near where i lived. despite what the media might tell you, you can't spot a predator by their race or class.

i was a funny looking, socially awkward uncool spotty little nerd with dirty second hand clothes and undiagnosed autism. i didn't fit in. the adults in my life weren't looking out for me. i slipped under so many radars it's unreal.

why am i telling you all this? because i know a truly frightening number of people who had the same experience. and most of them can't speak about it because of the stigma that comes with it. and the shame. 
it's not my shame. it's his. fuck that.

i'm talking because when we're silent about tough subjects as a society we leave space for bad narratives and lies, and those won't protect vulnerable people. the truth will. 
if you want to help, have these conversations with your mates, talk about the unimaginable horror of it and work out how to support and help survivors heal. we need to stop pretending this is rare. because i'm sorry, but it really isn't and it never has been.

#metoo

text:
hello kitty gone native and down to earth. 
in lombok, indonesia traditional potters star make potteries of hello kitty. 
smile is the international language, sign of i am ok, you are ok. 
friendship and kindness. 
hello kitty was here in an island faraway from japan. 
so far from home but she is home here in lombok, indonesia.

text:
.
tried. tried and failed.
empire of ignorance.
rule of power. dead.
you trample. batter.
through your grinder.
under boot heels.
choking grasp.
pounding fists.
still here. 
still beautiful. 
stronger than you.
stronger than hell.
.
.
poem "still here" by t.stark 
artwork by @stevenstahlberg
.

text:
dal 2012 ad oggi le donne uccise in italia per mano di un uomo sono 770. 
nel 2016 il 64,3% delle donne è stata uccisa dal coniuge (44,3%), dall’ex coniuge (16,5%) o dal partner/amante (3,5%).
nel 2018 fino ad ora, sono state uccise circa 50 donne.

qualcuno ricorda questi nomi?
elisa amato, morta per mano del fidanzato calciatore.
jenny reyes, sudamericana uccisa a genova per mano del marito.
imma stabile uccisa dal marito.
alessandra rifeser, uccisa dal compagno a coltellate.
luisa valli uccisa a 80 anni dal marito.
angela ferrara, uccisa brutalmente dal marito, guardia giurata.
maria zarba, uccisa dal marito a colpi di ascia.
tutte queste donne sono state uccise barbaramente dal "compagno di vita". l'ultimo sconcertante episodio pochi giorni fa, una sedicenne, desiree mariottini, uccisa per mano di alcuni ragazzi senegalesi e nigeriani irregolari, dopo essere stata ripetutamente violentata.

perche' vengono ricordate più facilmente coloro che sono state uccise da uomini di colore o immigrati? quando si parla di femmicidio il problema è l'uomo (se così possiamo chiamarlo) nient'altro.
.
.
.

e a voi donne dico di cercare di essere lucide e non farvi ingannare da due belle parole o un bel regalo. amate prima di tutto voi stesse, altrimenti non riusciretea far stare bene gli altri e potreste essere oggetto di manipolazione.
#femminicidio #stopabuse #nonunadipiu #metoo #woman #violence #red #picoftheday #photooftheday #life #live #family #love

text:
- hitman - 
mercredi dernier, nos amis de la boxe de rue sont venus faire les hitman pour nos amazones parisiennes.

le hitman permet de tester ses capacités en état de grand stress, dans un environnement sécurisé, dans des conditions les plus réalistes possible.

l'important n'est pas d'effectuer des techniques parfaites, de faire un "beau combat", de réussir à fuir sans avoir pris aucun coup, ni de mettre à terre son adversaire. 
l'essentiel du hitman est de faire preuve de détermination. 
de tenter des choses. de voir ses réactions face au stress. de se donner à 100%. de réaliser ce qu'on est capables de donner dans une situation de haut niveau de stress. de comprendre l'effet tunnel. 
de se gérer soi-même. 
si on gère ses émotions, c'est déjà plus de la moitié du travail de fait. 
et le plus efficace est de s'y confronter le plus souvent possible, pour essayer d'avancer au maximum. et s'y on rate, si on est déçu.e de sa performance, on y retourne, on n'abandonne pas. 
car nous progressons tou.te.s, chacun.e à notre rythme, mais en avant tout de même.

donc un enorme bravo aux amazones débutantes qui ont découvert le hitman, et aux confirmées qui ont testé un nouveau style de hitman. elles y ont toutes fait face avec une détermination dont toute notre équipe est plus que fière. 🥊🥊🥊✨✨✨🥊🥊🥊🥊🥊🥊🥊 #amazontrainingparis @adacfrance #sport #paris #selfdefensefeminine #selfdefensefemmes #harcèlement #hitman #artmartial #femmesfortes #respect #training #bestteam #selfdefenseforwomen #bestrong #mybodymychoice #metoo #autodefensefeminine #determination #confianceensoi #motivation #trainingday #fuite #combat

text:
in conversation with surabhi dhingra, president posco, on the #metoo movement … and empowering both women and men.  two startling facts stood out: - just by “saying no” and voicing discomfort, almost 70% - 80% of instances are resolved.  at times, many men are unaware of their actions.  women need to learn to say no and speak up firmly and unequivocally. - in companies in which posh training has been provided ... the incidences/complaint rates of sexual harassment are much lower than in those were training has not been given.  more education is needed for both men and women to curb the #metoo tide.  and just the simple philosophy of #respect.

#sippingthoughts #respect #posh #metoo #safety #poshca #justsayno #girlpower #training
name: Sukirti Gupta
tweet_full:
in conversation with surabhi dhingra, president posco, on the #metoo movement … and empowering both women and men.  two startling facts stood out: - just by “saying no” and voicing discomfort, almost 70% - 80% of instances are resolved.  at times, many men are unaware of their actions.  women need to learn to say no and speak up firmly and unequivocally. - in companies in which posh training has been provided ... the incidences/complaint rates of sexual harassment are much lower than in those were training has not been given.  more education is needed for both men and women to curb the #metoo tide.  and just the simple philosophy of #respect.

#sippingthoughts #respect #posh #metoo #safety #poshca #justsayno #girlpower #training

text:
#metoo: junior artist allegedly molested on 'housefull 4' sets
a female junior artist was allegedly molested on the sets of 'housefull 4' on thursday night. narrating her ordeal, the victim said in an interview that she was sitting with a colleague on the sets of the movie, when two men namely, pawan shetty, sagar along with four other men came and began misbehaving with her friend. soon things got uglier. the miscreants also got hold of the complainant and touched her inappropriately, when she tried to intervene. "i was sitting with a colleague when suddenly two men, pawan shetty and sagar, with four others came and tried to take away my colleague forcefully. when i tried to stop them, shetty started pushing me and touched my private parts," the junior artist said. "when i started screaming, the production people and actors akshay kumar and riteish deshmukh, came outside. they only gave us the idea that we should call the police. the accused men ran away when they saw the production people and others," she added. a first information report (fir) has been registered. the fourth installment of the 'housefull' franchise has been in news since weeks after actor nana patekar and director sajid khan were accused of sexual misconduct in the wake of the ongoing #metoo movement in india. after the allegations surfaced against them, both patekar and khan announced their exit from the film.

text:
forgiveness does not mean you erase the past, or forget what has happened. it doesn’t even mean the other person will change his/her behavior – you cannot control that. all it means is that you are letting go of the anger and pain.
•
dear [blank],
•
i forgive you for [state whatever you feel has caused you the greatest emotional distress and anguish]. i forgive myself for letting it happen. for doing too little. for doing to much. i forgive myself for times i felt paralyzed, and could do nothing at all. •
with love and empowerment to myself,
[your name]
•
be as completely honest as you can. write it all down. you are not going to send this letter. you are the only person who will ever read it. so purge all the negative and pent up unsaid feelings and – let loose. it’s important to write it all down. saying it to yourself in your head does not make it “real” enough. write it down. scratch into the paper, tear pages if necessary. again, no one will ever see what you have written, so do not be afraid to get personal.
•
once you have finished, it is time to forgive one more person; yourself. you did the best you could. forgive yourself for letting it happen. for doing to little. for doing to much. or, forgive yourself for doing nothing at all. whatever happened, forgive yourself. you cannot change the past, or how you reacted in that times. you can only learn.
•
forgiveness is so important as the first step because it signifies a mental shift from being a victim to being the master of your life and having complete control over your destiny. you make the decision to forgive the person. you make the decision you are going to move on with your life. you are now taking action instead of simply reacting. you are in the process of taking back your power and being the master.
•
with love, marie
•
•

text:
"blackbirds singing in the dead of night,
take these broken wings and learn to fly,
all your life, you were only waiting for this moment to arise."
.
"yesterday" was however when "all my troubles seemed" to gang up on me. but as the doctor said wrt rosa parks, "we have to not help her," i believe life has been doing the same to me. 
today started with me reporting an arse who misused my data and intruded my privacy yesterday, to the company he works for, which so irresponsibly mismanaged my data and have no notion of data protection and privacy policies of eu, such that they shared my number in such a way that this scumbag had the audacity to text me for unprofessional reasons. lectured the company about data protection and the ramifications of the violation of privacy and data protection especially when it is intrusion of privacy and threatening of safety or personal space of not just women but any human being anywhere. reported plagiarism of some of my students earlier this week. this week was a bad one. and it seems my supervisor is right about me about the "all your life, you were only waiting for this moment [to become the 'little rebel' (she calls me that at times)] to arrive" part. 
maybe things really need to go a little above our tolerance limit to get us to react. maybe sometimes not getting any help when we really need it is the best way that we can level up and then can help many others... that, or just cast a death glare or curse the scumbags such that they run, afterall "demons run when a good man (or human) goes to war." #beatles #blackbird #yesterday #dataprotection #metoo #alpine #alpinecough #birdsofinstagram #doctorwho

#جون_ابراهام يخرج اسم #فيكي_سيدانا من فيلمه #باتالا_هاوس . بسبب حملة #مي_تو . .
.
في أعقاب حملة #metoo ، قرر كل من جون ابراهام و نيخيل ادفاني والمنتج بوشان كومار إسقاط اسم المخرج فيكي سيدانا من قائمة فيلم في باتالا هاوس. بسبب اتهام فيكي بسوء السلوك الجنسي من قبل الممثله كريتيكا شارما بمحاولة الاغتصاب في عام 2013.  وأصدر مصدر قريب من شركة الإنتاج "فيكي سيدانا كان من طاقم الاخراج لـ باتالا هاوس. في ضوء الادعاءات الخطيرة ضد سيدانا والتحقيق الجاري في الشرطة ، قرر جون و نيخيل وبوشان إسقاط اسمه من المشروع بسبب فعل الذي قام به ، على الرغم من أن العقد المبرم معه ، إلا أن دار الإنتاج تريد أن تعبر عن تضامنها مع النساء المتضررات. هم يفكرون في خيارات للتنازل عنها ".
.
. .
. .
. .
. .
. . . .

जॉन अब्राहम बटाला हाउस से विकी सिडाना का नाम छोड़ देता है। एक और #metoo दुर्घटना .
. . . 
#johnabraham drops #vickysidana’s name from #batlahouse. another #metoo casualty ‏in the wake of #metoo movement, john abraham, nikkhil advani and producer bhushan kumar have decided to drop casting director vicky sidana’s name from the credit roll of batla house. vicky has been accused of sexual misconduct by two survivors and actor kritika sharma accused him of attempted rape in 2013. ‏a source close to the production informed the leading tabloid, "vicky sidana was the casting director on board batla house. in light of the grave allegations against sidana and the ongoing police investigation, john, nikkhil and bhushan have decided to drop his name from the final credit roll. he can't be fired from the project because his job is already done. although the contract drawn with him states that he be credited for his work, the production house wants to express their solidarity with the aggrieved women. so, they are considering options to wiggle out of it." .
. . . .
.

.3 . .

.

#جون_ابراهام يخرج اسم #فيكي_سيدانا من فيلمه #باتالا_هاوس . بسبب حملة #مي_تو . .
.
في أعقاب حملة #metoo ، قرر كل من جون ابراهام و نيخيل ادفاني والمنتج بوشان كومار إسقاط اسم المخرج فيكي سيدانا من قائمة فيلم في باتالا هاوس. بسبب اتهام فيكي بسوء السلوك الجنسي من قبل الممثله كريتيكا شارما بمحاولة الاغتصاب في عام 2013.  وأصدر مصدر قريب من شركة الإنتاج "فيكي سيدانا كان من طاقم الاخراج لـ باتالا هاوس. في ضوء الادعاءات الخطيرة ضد سيدانا والتحقيق الجاري في الشرطة ، قرر جون و نيخيل وبوشان إسقاط اسمه من المشروع بسبب فعل الذي قام به ، على الرغم من أن العقد المبرم معه ، إلا أن دار الإنتاج تريد أن تعبر عن تضامنها مع النساء المتضررات. هم يفكرون في خيارات للتنازل عنها ".
.
. .
. .
. .
. .
. . . .

जॉन अब्राहम बटाला हाउस से विकी सिडाना का नाम छोड़ देता है। एक और #metoo दुर्घटना .
. . . 
#johnabraham drops #vickysidana’s name from #batlahouse. another #metoo casualty ‏in the wake of #metoo movement, john abraham, nikkhil advani and producer bhushan kumar have decided to drop casting director vicky sidana’s name from the credit roll of batla house. vicky has been accused of sexual misconduct by two survivors and actor kritika sharma accused him of attempted rape in 2013. ‏a source close to the production informed the leading tabloid, "vicky sidana was the casting director on board batla house. in light of the grave allegations against sidana and the ongoing police investigation, john, nikkhil and bhushan have decided to drop his name from the final credit roll. he can not be fired from the project because his job is already done. although the contract drawn with him states that he be credited for his work, the production house wants to express their solidarity with the aggrieved women. so, they are considering options to wiggle out of it." .
. . . .
.

text:
woman, you are free to be wild! . 
a little video clip of me giving a talk and signing of my latest book ‘in my heart i know’, at the women, waistline, & wellness event, sharing the importance of allowing our heart to guide us and how society ‘tries’ to stop us wild awakened women from being confident, spiritual and sexy, speaking up, and shining our light...
.
not on my watch!
.
when i’m standing up speaking, teaching, sharing, or inspiring others, i love knowing that by speaking my truth, being my truth, and expressing my truth i’m helping other women feel comfortable and safe with standing in their truth also, but the thing i love the most is seeing the connection, the nods, the pain turning into peace by the light in their eyes, and the moments of ‘me too’ upon their faces, knowing they are not alone, and it’s also in these moments i feel i’m not alone too.
.
recently i’ve been going through my own ‘labour pains of life’, like we all do when change is occurring, life is evolving, and shifts are awakening, and although there is some struggle there is so much beauty and freedom i feel emerging, as my heart reminds me that this woman has more faith than fear! .
🌹
•
•
•
#speakup #express #truth #freedom #liberation #trust #faith #empoweredwoman #awake #inspired #heart #courage #strength #metoo #connection

text:
bannon wanted to use the sorts of aggressive messaging tactics usually reserved for geopolitical conflicts to move the us electorate further to the right, wylie said. he had already directed a series of anti-establishment, conservative documentary films and presided over the far-right website breitbart news, but cambridge analytica would mark another step in his overall ambitions to transform the nation.

with financial backing from hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer, bannon co-founded cambridge analytica in 2013 as the us-branch of strategic communication laboratories (scl) group, a british company that advertises how it has conducted "behavioral change" programs in more than 60 countries.

wylie described cambridge analytica as - steve bannon and robert mercer using a foreign, military contractor ... to use some of the same techniques that the military uses ... on the american electorate.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan and drew griffin
cnn

text:
in 2014, steve bannon – then executive chairman of the “alt-right” news network breitbart – was christopher wylie’s boss. and robert mercer, the secretive us hedge-fund billionaire and republican donor, was cambridge analytica’s investor. and the idea they bought into was to bring big data and social media to an established military methodology – “information operations” – then turn it on the us electorate.

cambridge analytica’s parent company, scl, had won contracts with the us state department and was pitching to the pentagon, and wylie was genuinely freaked out. - it’s insane, he told me one night. - the company has created psychological profiles of 230 million americans. and now they want to work with the pentagon? it’s like nixon on steroids.

carole cadwalladr
the guardian

text:
wylie said that bannon's plans began to solidify in 2014, when cambridge analytica consulted various republican campaigns and pacs ahead of the midterm elections. the company began to test and apply its psychographics by using facebook data to model individuals' personality types in order to understand how to influence them.

documents show the john bolton super pac, which promoted candidates supported by recently appointed white house national security adviser john bolton, paid cambridge analytical $454,700 in 2014 for "behavioral microtargeting with psychographic messaging." those services included strategies that broke individual voters into "clusters" based on what messages would resonate with them.

wylie also said the company used focus groups and messaging trials in 2014 to test some of the concepts that became core themes of the trump campaign, such as "drain the swamp" and imagery of walls. "a lot of the narratives of the trump campaign were what we were testing in 2014," wylie said.

he added that bannon directly presided over much of the company's initial research. "everything that we were doing ultimately had to be passed up to bannon for approval," said wylie, who left the company in late 2014.

wylie said bannon would fly to london about once a month for company meetings, and during that time he came to understand bannon's ideology. "he really liked the idea of using a military-style approach to changing people's perceptions," wylie said.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan & drew griffin
cnn

text:
bannon wanted to use the sorts of aggressive messaging tactics usually reserved for geopolitical conflicts to move the us electorate further to the right, wylie said. he had already directed a series of anti-establishment, conservative documentary films and presided over the far-right website breitbart news, but cambridge analytica would mark another step in his overall ambitions to transform the nation.

with financial backing from hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer, bannon co-founded cambridge analytica in 2013 as the us-branch of strategic communication laboratories (scl) group, a british company that advertises how it has conducted "behavioral change" programs in more than 60 countries.

wylie described cambridge analytica as - steve bannon and robert mercer using a foreign, military contractor ... to use some of the same techniques that the military uses ... on the american electorate.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan and drew griffin
cnn

text:
in 2014, steve bannon – then executive chairman of the “alt-right” news network breitbart – was christopher wylie’s boss. and robert mercer, the secretive us hedge-fund billionaire and republican donor, was cambridge analytica’s investor. and the idea they bought into was to bring big data and social media to an established military methodology – “information operations” – then turn it on the us electorate.

cambridge analytica’s parent company, scl, had won contracts with the us state department and was pitching to the pentagon, and wylie was genuinely freaked out. - it’s insane, he told me one night. - the company has created psychological profiles of 230 million americans. and now they want to work with the pentagon? it’s like nixon on steroids.

tweet_full:
in 2014, steve bannon – then executive chairman of the “alt-right” news network breitbart – was christopher wylie’s boss. and robert mercer, the secretive us hedge-fund billionaire and republican donor, was cambridge analytica’s investor. and the idea they bought into was to bring big data and social media to an established military methodology – “information operations” – then turn it on the us electorate.

cambridge analytica’s parent company, scl, had won contracts with the us state department and was pitching to the pentagon, and wylie was genuinely freaked out. - it’s insane, he told me one night. - the company has created psychological profiles of 230 million americans. and now they want to work with the pentagon? it’s like nixon on steroids.

carole cadwalladr

text:
wylie said that bannon's plans began to solidify in 2014, when cambridge analytica consulted various republican campaigns and pacs ahead of the midterm elections. the company began to test and apply its psychographics by using facebook data to model individuals' personality types in order to understand how to influence them.

documents show the john bolton super pac, which promoted candidates supported by recently appointed white house national security adviser john bolton, paid cambridge analytical $454,700 in 2014 for "behavioral microtargeting with psychographic messaging." those services included strategies that broke individual voters into "clusters" based on what messages would resonate with them.

wylie also said the company used focus groups and messaging trials in 2014 to test some of the concepts that became core themes of the trump campaign, such as "drain the swamp" and imagery of walls. "a lot of the narratives of the trump campaign were what we were testing in 2014," wylie said.

he added that bannon directly presided over much of the company's initial research. "everything that we were doing ultimately had to be passed up to bannon for approval," said wylie, who left the company in late 2014.

wylie said bannon would fly to london about once a month for company meetings, and during that time he came to understand bannon's ideology. "he really liked the idea of using a military-style approach to changing people's perceptions," wylie said.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan & drew griffin
cnn

text: in unserer neuen ausgabe: nachdenken über igor levit, weltstar, wegbegleiter und politischster aller pianisten, von georg diez. opfer-bingo zu #metoo von nina kunz. ausserdem: familienleben ist ein rollenspiel, bei dem man sich seine rolle nicht auswählen kann. man wird als tochter oder sohn geboren, wechselt dann vielleicht mal zu einem schwierigeren part, der heisst dann mutter oder vater, aber ablegen kann man keine dieser rollen. für dieses heft hat sich der niederländische schriftsteller arnon grünberg etwas aussergewöhnliches ausgedacht: er wollte unbedingt einmal vater auf zeit spielen, also ist er selbst auf familien zugegangen mit dem angebot, als ersatzvater zu wirken. sein text ist deshalb interessant, weil die distanz der nichtbiologischen vaterschaft es ihm besser ermöglicht, sozusagen im feldversuch darüber nachzudenken, was eine familie im kern ausmacht. tolstois viel zitierter satz aus «anna karenina», wonach alle glücklichen familien einander gleichen, die unglücklichen jedoch alle auf ihre eigene weise unglücklich sind, stimmt natürlich nicht: selbst im glück ist jede familie absolut einzigartig. wir wünschen ihnen viel vergnügen und vor allem ein schönes wochenende! titelfoto: mustafah abdulaziz #tagimagi #dasmagazin #georgdiez #arnongrünberg #familie #reportage #igorlevit #mustafahabdulaziz @georgdiez @ninaznuk @mustafahabdulaziz @grunberg_embedded

text:
in his first post-white house interviews, steve bannon, the rightwing ideologue who helped propel donald trump to the white house, made clear that he had no intention of going quietly. - i’ve got my hands back on my weapons, the former white house chief strategist, who returned as executive chairman of breitbart news late friday afternoon, told the weekly standard. - i built a f***ing machine at breitbart. and now i’m about to go back, knowing what i know, and we’re about to rev that machine up. and rev it up we will do.

just hours after his departure from the trump administration became public, breitbart, whose traffic and advertising have fallen significantly since trump’s election, trumpeted the return of their “populist hero” on its homepage. - the populist-nationalist movement got a lot stronger today, breitbart editor-in-chief alex marlow said in the publication’s announcement post. - breitbart gained an executive chairman with his finger on the pulse of the trump agenda.

the fall of steve bannon is a win for the globalists. but will it last?

also on friday, the once-again head of breitbart told bloomberg news: - if there’s any confusion out there, let me clear it up: i’m leaving the white house and going to war for trump against his opponents – on capitol hill, in the media, and in corporate america.

the 63-year-old also retains the backing of hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer. the pair met on wednesday to plot their future plans, bloomberg reported.

julia carrie wong
the guardian

text:
i look like a boss right? confident, happy, sexy….well.

im going to let you all into a little secret…some days i don’t feel like a boss….i feel like a  really tired mum to 2 crazy little boys…somedays i don’t actually know how i get through the day…if the kids aren’t screaming someone is trying to sabotage miba, if its not miba its my asshole neighbours or nobhead ex. 
the last few weeks have been pretty crazy and today especially has been a bit of a rollercoaster. literally highs and lows all day. so why am i telling you this…well…first of all i want you to see that its normal to have a shitty time,but…what has pulled me back every single day is the messages from you guys. you’ve made your 1st sale on instagram, you’ve dare to bid for a huge project and won the contract, you managed to get through the day without screaming fuck you at someone all the wins, no matter how big or small,we celebrate with you and feel so proud!

if i died tomorrow and knew sharing my journey had helped just 1 person i would be happy. but it appears theres more than just one or two of you that we have inspired with our miba movement!

not a day goes by that we take a single one of our supporters for granted…its very rare we actually sit and really take stock of whats really going on…but today has been one of those days…a reality slap in the face…and so i wanted to say….you got this….use miba for everything that its worth…binge watch the videos, connect with your fellow mibs, build relationships and continue to love and support each other. 
you ladies are what makes miba, miba…we ( i think im ok to talk on behalf of leona here ) thank you from the bottom of our hearts!

incredible hair and make up by fellow mibs natalie boland and melanie rose photo by rob gurney

text:
in his first post-white house interviews, steve bannon, the rightwing ideologue who helped propel donald trump to the white house, made clear that he had no intention of going quietly. - i’ve got my hands back on my weapons, the former white house chief strategist, who returned as executive chairman of breitbart news late friday afternoon, told the weekly standard. - i built a f***ing machine at breitbart. and now i’m about to go back, knowing what i know, and we’re about to rev that machine up. and rev it up we will do.

just hours after his departure from the trump administration became public, breitbart, whose traffic and advertising have fallen significantly since trump’s election, trumpeted the return of their “populist hero” on its homepage. - the populist-nationalist movement got a lot stronger today, breitbart editor-in-chief alex marlow said in the publication’s announcement post. - breitbart gained an executive chairman with his finger on the pulse of the trump agenda.

the fall of steve bannon is a win for the globalists. but will it last?

also on friday, the once-again head of breitbart told bloomberg news: - if there’s any confusion out there, let me clear it up: i’m leaving the white house and going to war for trump against his opponents – on capitol hill, in the media, and in corporate america.

the 63-year-old also retains the backing of hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer. the pair met on wednesday to plot their future plans, bloomberg reported.

julia carrie wong
the guardian

@regran_ed from @jasperhousehaiti - "for the woman whose husband makes an "extra stop" after work every evening.⠀
⠀
for the woman who is mourning the loss of a pregnancy that nobody else knew about.⠀
⠀
for the woman who still leads from the front even although she’s lost inside.⠀
⠀
for the woman who has wanted to end it all but found strength to carry on.⠀
⠀
for the woman sleeping next to a stranger every night.⠀
⠀
for the woman that endures one broken relationship after another because there was no father around to teach her what love looks like.⠀
⠀
for every single woman that cries in the shower so that nobody else can see. because if you aren't strong-nobody is.⠀
⠀
just because the water washes your tears doesn't mean that you don't cry. just because you cry doesn’t mean that you’re not strong enough to handle it.⠀
⠀
i am you. i see you. i am with you, i cry with you. i love you."⠀
⠀
excerpts from: brittany latham⠀

text:
#metoo अभियान के तहत बॉलीवुड में खुले तौर पर कई महिला कलाकारों ने अपनी आपबीती शेयर की हैं. अब टीवी शो 'दिल से दिल तक' फेम जैस्मीन भसीन ने अपनी आपबीती सुनाते हुए बताया कि एक डायरेक्टर ने उनसे कपड़े उतारने को कहा था. जैस्मीन ने कहा. "हमें यौन उत्पीड़न के बारे में बात करने के लिए मजबूत होने की जरूरत है. कोई भी इससे इनकार नहीं कर सकता है कि यौन उत्पीड़न नहीं है. लड़कियों को पता होना चाहिए कि कैसे ऐसी परिस्थितियों से लड़ना है.”

text:
- bannon got it immediately. he believes in the whole andrew breitbart doctrine that politics is downstream from culture, so to change politics you need to change culture. and fashion trends are a useful proxy for that. trump is like a pair of uggs, or crocs, basically. so how do you get from people thinking ‘ugh. totally ugly’ to the moment when everyone is wearing them? that was the inflection point he was looking for.

is what cambridge analytica does akin to bullying? - i think it’s worse than bullying, christopher wylie says. - because people don’t necessarily know it’s being done to them. at least bullying respects the agency of people because they know. so it’s worse, because if you do not respect the agency of people, anything that you’re doing after that point is not conducive to a democracy. and fundamentally, information warfare is not conducive to democracy.

millions of people’s personal information was stolen and used to target them in ways they wouldn’t have seen, and couldn’t have known about, by a mercenary outfit, cambridge analytica, who, wylie says, “would work for anyone”. who would pitch to russian oil companies. would they subvert elections abroad on behalf of foreign governments?

it occurs to me to ask wylie this one night. - yes.

nato or non-nato? - either. i mean they’re mercenaries. they’ll work for pretty much anyone who pays.

it’s an incredible revelation. it also encapsulates all of the problems of outsourcing – at a global scale, with added cyberweapons. and in the middle of it all are the public – our intimate family connections, our “likes”, our crumbs of personal data, all sucked into a swirling black hole that’s expanding and growing and is now owned by a politically motivated

carole cadwall
the guardian

text:
- bannon got it immediately. he believes in the whole andrew breitbart doctrine that politics is downstream from culture, so to change politics you need to change culture. and fashion trends are a useful proxy for that. trump is like a pair of uggs, or crocs, basically. so how do you get from people thinking ‘ugh. totally ugly’ to the moment when everyone is wearing them? that was the inflection point he was looking for.

is what cambridge analytica does akin to bullying? - i think it’s worse than bullying, christopher wylie says. - because people don’t necessarily know it’s being done to them. at least bullying respects the agency of people because they know. so it’s worse, because if you do not respect the agency of people, anything that you’re doing after that point is not conducive to a democracy. and fundamentally, information warfare is not conducive to democracy.

millions of people’s personal information was stolen and used to target them in ways they wouldn’t have seen, and couldn’t have known about, by a mercenary outfit, cambridge analytica, who, wylie says, “would work for anyone”. who would pitch to russian oil companies. would they subvert elections abroad on behalf of foreign governments?

it occurs to me to ask wylie this one night. - yes.

nato or non-nato? - either. i mean they’re mercenaries. they’ll work for pretty much anyone who pays.

it’s an incredible revelation. it also encapsulates all of the problems of outsourcing – at a global scale, with added cyberweapons. and in the middle of it all are the public – our intimate family connections, our “likes”, our crumbs of personal data, all sucked into a swirling black hole that’s expanding and growing and is now owned by a politically motivated billionaire.

carole cadwalladr
the guardian

text:
india needs to learn how to deal with sexual misconduct from google's ceo sundar pichai

google ceo sundar pichai on thursday said the company fired 48 employees over the past two years due to allegations of sexual misconduct. the employees included 13 senior executives, pichai said in a statement. "in recent years, we've made a number of changes, including taking an increasingly hard line on inappropriate conduct by people in positions of authority," pichai said

google's andy rubin the man behind android creation had received a severance package of $90 million (€79 million) after a google employee accused him of sexual misconduct. "we are dead serious about making we provide a safe and inclusive workplace. we want to assure you that we review every single complaint about sexual harassment or inappropriate conduct, we investigate and we take action," he added.

#metoo #google #sexualmisconduct #timeforjustice #learn #smartaction #nomoreviolation #sundarpichai #andyrubin #women #safety #workculture #safeenvironment

text:
#longpostalert 
the culture and tradition of india is considered as old and great all over the world where people used to worship various female goddesses, saints and poets. india is also a powerful nation and famous worldwide for being the largest democracy in the world however, women backwardness is also very clear in the indian society because of the social issues, problems and lots of restrictions against women.

in indian schools, we learn something called value education or moral science (as it used to be called in convent schools). the idea behind this training was for children to learn not to steal or cheat, to be honest, brave and so on. maybe twice a week we read out loud in class — a paragraph each — from our moral science textbooks as the teacher looked on.

a quarter of a century later, i still don’t know what i was supposed to learn from those texts. often the reading, the pace of which varied with the student reading, was interrupted by the teacher essentially repeating what was written in the textbooks. i do, however, know one thing — not one of those classes or lines or paragraphs or chapters taught me that as a girl i could make my own decisions, dress how i liked and that i was equal to the boys in my class.

be it going to a temple when i menstruate or grabbing a smoke in public or rather how i choose to dress, should be my choice and that shouldn't be the reason, why one chose to abuse me. 
no i am not saying smoking or anything else in my post should be justified, but rather a choice. stop staring and cat calling me on the streets when i grab a smoke or wear clothes which might at times reveal a bit too much.

#oh_the_sanity_in_me.

..
..
..
me da asco y me repugna solamente pensar que sigue habiendo micromachismo en una profesión donde la gran mayoría somos mujeres.

en el caso de que te pase a ti denuncia no nos cayos a quedar calladas 🤫
..
..
..
desde @silvia_fisioterapia apoyamos el movimiento #metoofisioterapia #metoo
si quiere final feliz siempre tendremos las agujas ya veras que gran final feliz.

text:
sometimes, like now, i can’t believe that this is me 😢... that this is me wearing real smiles and not haboring torment on the inside... that this is me chaste and not stuck in a situationship looking for validation... that this is me sane enough to know when i’m being taken advantage of... that this is me healthy enough to know that not everyone is against me and out to get me... that this is me capable of guarding my space and bold enough to send out people with negative vibes... that this is me confident about my occasional stutter when i share my story... that this is me healed enough to help others heal... that this is me giving and doing the things i do. wholeness, sure, is real and attainable regardless of where you’re presently at. i can teach you how i did it. send me an email. ✉️ akanofaith@gmail.com

text:
i choose to set out each day with high vibrations.
to follow through and hope they spread.
i choose to put the past away, the past is dead!
i choose to sit quietly when i need to.
i will not allow my anxiety to manifest into a manic episode.
i will breath i will yoga i will listen to my body not my mind.
i will not allow what i perceive others to think.

i want to continue my journey in opening the third eye.
i am worthy 
i am smart
i am beautiful 
i am kind
i am fun
i can be happy

i am 'me too'. this will not define me. 
remember the past is dead 
each day comes with a new beginning to start over
start vibrating higher to achieve what i love and would want to do for employment 
i smile and know its for the best
i am getting there . . .
... 😊 🌈. 🌈. 🌈 . #thankyoujesus
#grateful
#blessed .
🙏. amazing good days are coming!
#everydayisamentalhealthday #metoo #iamagirl

text:
— the concept of touring is peculiar in that it implies a displacement: the artist leaves their home to come to another person’s home, where they, essentially, share observations made elsewhere, at another time. on top of that, the works we (@ccap_sthlm and @coff_sthlm) came to motala to share are hands-on (i.e. interactive), which is, in itself, an ethically messy paradigm; especially regarding the notion of consent in the time of #metoo. one shouldn’t be surprised to thing that a practice like touring an interactive work is anything but obnoxious.

except that every once in a while a group of strangers will meet in the fictional forest (#träd) and enjoy each-other’s company; sometimes making it possible for individuals to have a transformative experience; sometimes creating the conditions for individuals to be moved to tears; sometimes creating the conditions for the collective to inspire the sense of belonging in every attending individual.

which is an incredibly sentimental thing to say, except that what i’m trying to get at is not as simple as sentiment. what i am trying to get at is the sense of relief the consequences of which is political.

when a group of individuals becomes sensitised to their bodily experience and their bodily experience of the collective, of the group, of a small-scale society: their behaviour changes. reportedly, people become more empathetic, gentle, curious, available to touch, generous, and respectful. to say the least. which are spectacular qualities to experience at the level of a collective.

and so we persist and insist and study and make adjustments and initiate and observe and listen and make adjustments and ... keep on touring.

the situation is far from ideal. but possibly worth the investment.

questionmark.

text:
η ρωσική αστυνομία αδιαφορεί για τα θύματα ενδοοικογενειακής βίας
#ανθρώπιναδικαιώματα #ενδοοικογενειακήβία #μκο #ρωσία
__________
τις χτυπούν, τις καίνε ή τις στραγγαλίζουν κι όμως τα θύματα ενδοοικογενειακής βίας στη ρωσία βρίσκονται συχνά αντιμέτωπα με την αδιαφορία της αστυνομίας και με «σημαντικά κενά του δικαστικού συστήματος», καταγγέλλει σε μια έκθεση, που έδωσε στη δημοσιότητα, η μκο παρατηρητήριο ανθρωπίνων δικαιωμάτων. 
με τίτλο «μπορώ να σε σκοτώσω και κανείς δε με συλλαμβάνει», η έκθεση επικαλείται τις μαρτυρίες 27 γυναικών που αφηγούνται τη σωματική και ψυχολογική κόλαση που βίωσαν. 
σε αντιπαραβολή με το κίνημα #metoo, οι ρωσικές αρχές αποποινικοποίησαν το 2017 ορισμένες μορφές ενδοοικογενειακής βίας προκειμένου, σύμφωνα με τους προασπιστές του μέτρου, να προστατεύσουν τις «παραδοσιακές αξίες». η έκθεση της human rights watch, όπως αναφέρει το απε-μπε, συγκρίνει αυτήν την αποποινικοποίηση με μια «λευκή επιταγή» στους βίαιους συζύγους. δικηγόροι και οργανώσεις προάσπισης των κακοποιημένων γυναικών που αναφέρονται στην έκθεση παρατήρησαν έπειτα από αυτό το μέτρο μια αύξηση των εκκλήσεων για βοήθεια. 
η μη κυβερνητική οργάνωση καταγγέλλει επίσης «σοβαρά κενά στο δικαστικό σύστημα», όπως την απουσία συγκεκριμένων ποινικών κυρώσεων σε εθνικό επίπεδο για τα περιστατικά ενδοοικογενειακής βίας, όπως και μια κουλτούρα ενοχοποίησης των θυμάτων, με την αστυνομία να απειλεί «συχνά» τα θύματα ή να μην καταγράφει τις καταγγελίες τους. 
για παράδειγμα, μια γυναίκα κατήγγειλε ότι υπήρξε θύμα ενδοοικογενειακής βίας τουλάχιστον 20 φορές, χωρίς να εισακουστεί, προτού ο σύζυγός της επιχειρήσει να την στραγγαλίσει. εκείνη τον χτύπησε με ένα σφυρί. την ώρα που η μήνυσή της κρίθηκε μη αποδεκτή, εκείνη του συντρόφου της έχει πάρει τον δρόμο της δικαιοσύνης, σύμφωνα με την έκθεση του παρατηρητηρίου. 
στην έκθεση αναφέρεται επίσης και η υπόθεση μιας γυναίκας που κάλεσε την αστυνομία μετά τις απειλές του συντρόφου της ότι θα την σκοτώσει, το 2016. μια αστυνομικός πήγε στο σημείο και της είπε να «μην ανησυχεί». σύμφωνα με τη μκο zona prava, την άτυχη γυναίκα σκότωσε ο σύντροφός της πέντε λεπτά ...

text: today was the first day in literal years that i ran around looking all cute and shit and introducing myself as kairi. i feel liberated beyond words. i'm not going to allow my #metoo story to keep me from being me anymore. for too long i allowed the actions of a man cause me to be afraid of being myself. for too long i allowed the fact that i reported to the cops that i'd been raped and have them do nothing about it but tell me i was making it up (even though the rape kit proved otherwise) keep me from being my true self. i allowed my boyfriend at the time who belittled me and not believe me keep me from being able to continue transitioning. for too long i was afraid to continue becoming a woman because i thought if i stopped it would never happen again. here i am, six years later, no longer afraid. i am kairi. #fuckthepatriarchy #lgbtqia #mtf #mtftransgender

text:
✨trade your busy life for a full one✨

this is such a thought provoking 💭 article. it seems no one is too busy to tell you how busy they are. 
written by courtney carver

it might not seem like it at first, but a full life looks very different from a busy life. 💕🕊 a busy life is …

frantic
exhausting
ineffective
stressful
diluted
scattered

a busy life distracts us from what we really care about, and who we really care about. a busy life is all about piling it on, catching up, falling behind, and waking up tired to do it all over again.

a full life is …

meaningful
thoughtful
interesting
passionate
focused
present

a full life invites us to engage in what we really care about, and spend time with who we really care about. a full life isn’t about doing it all, but falling asleep at the end of the day content with how you spent your minutes and hours and a pleasant anticipation of the day to come.

trade your busy life for a full one

a busy life leads to jaw clenching and brow furrowing. a full life encourages you to smile and breathe. the success of a busy life is measured by check marks on a to-do list while the success of a full life is measured by what’s on your heart.

choose a full life.

a busy life seemingly chooses us, but we get to intentionally choose a full life by identifying what matters and getting rid of what doesn’t.

a full life allows you to show all the way up for people you love, create the time and space to listen to your heart and soul, and finally connect with what matters most.

text: i wish i could convey how appreciative i am of everyone who has embraced me as of late. i’m still figuring out what it means to be whole again, and it’s a messy bumpy ride. but for the first time since i was little i feel ok. i feel like it’s ok for me to occupy space, and i’m tying to just be comfortable being myself. to not be the groomed victim, but to be the thriving survivor. i’m so proud of my friends who have faced the last few months with bravery as we’ve watched daily as people dissect the impact of sexual abuse in the open. who have braved every triggering moment. who have asked such hard questions and have opened dialogues about what it means to find healing and what forms of justice we need and deserve. we’ve got a long way to go, but starting is nearly always the hardest part. you’re loved. never forget that. #metoo #latenightthoughts

text:
by the age of 14 i was living away from home.

at 16 i finished year 12 - a full two years younger than my peers.

at 18, i walked away from a car accident where the car rolled 6 times which left me with acute traumatic brain injury, severe whiplash that still causes me pain, and ptsd.

at 21, i was sexually assaulted by a healthcare professional. 
at 23, i lost an intimate partner to suicide 2 weeks after we broke up. 
at 26, i packed up my whole life and moved interstate away from all of my friends and family for a relationship that wound up being toxic, and i stayed there for 10 years until i worked up enough courage to leave. 
at 27 i experienced post-natal depression after i became a mother with zero support network.

at 28, i launched an e-commerce business that grew into something phenomenal. 
at 31, i lost 20kgs, competed in ifbb physique at the arnold sports festival australia, in the same year that i packed up the entire activewear online warehouse solo, organised to exhibit at the expo and looked after a 4 year old while i did it. 
at 32, i become a published author. 
at 33, i found the courage to stand on my own and left a bad relationship. i experienced anxiety, severe depression, and suicidal thoughts while i grieved the loss of the family i'd always wanted and helped a 6 year old through his parents divorce. 
at 36, i'm the happiest, strongest, most confident, and most mentally healthy i've ever been. i live my truth, i own my faults, and i have the best self worth i've ever had. for the first time, i love myself and the person that i am. good, bad, and weird parts combined. 
and all this doesn't even comprise the entirety of what i've achieved or overcome. so now, i use what i've learned to help others - i share my stories and my techniques for overcoming to inspire, uplift, and heal people as best i can. i regularly say i'm an exceptional human. 
i'd love for you to feel that great about yourself too. 
come and join us: @the.strong.woman.project ------------
charity lunch + guest speakers + the strong woman project launch!
3rd nov, 11am @ miss bliss wholefoods kitchen, 85 vulture st #1 west end, brisbane

text:
जिस तरह कुछ महिलाओं ने जिन्होंने पहले आवाज नही उठायी अब जाकर #metoo campaign चलाया है और पुरुषों की लंपटता को उजागर किया जा रहा है, उसी तरह यदि पुरुषों ने भी #youtoo campaign चला दिया और सारे छुपे रिश्ते उजागर कर दिए और पुरानी मोहब्बतें/मुलाकातें उजागर कर दीं तो पता नहीं कितनी सती-सावित्रियाँ आत्महत्या को मजबूर हो जाएंगी.
कितने वैवाहिक जीवन नष्ट हो जाएंगे.
न जाने कितने बच्चे अपनी माँओं से नफरत करने लग जाएंगे. 🤔

एक विचार.
वो कहते है ना. अकेले हम ही नहीं
शामिल इस जुर्म में, नजरें जब मिली
मुस्कुराये तुम भी थे 😋

text:
and what's alarming? racism is pitched as a minority issue when it's **factually** a white issue, and has subsequently left white people unprepared to even consider the reality of diversity, which is not actually scary; diversity is a predictable outcome of the principals american was founded on
.

ironically -- and i *study* white people and i still don't talk about trump, i just make fun of kanye instead, trump has capitalized on terrorism to incite fear among the extreme right (...and meg newman and megan kelly and the 3 million "other" liberal white woman) to make white people think they're facing genocide... theyre not; it's just a natural, very predictable, outcome of a democracy, and a staple feature of our nation
.

and the real fear of this "change of guards" is not actually a "divided country", bc ...um, that's jusf another staple of america, but that it's inadvertently accelerating the a strange total earsure of white dominance -- everyone from charlie rose to rosanne barre is going extinct; the genocide white poor people think brown people are causing is just actively shit white people are doing to each other; trumps antics are making white america bing eat each other
.

it's not normal that the white girl "movement" is adding simple "offensive" conversations to the #metoo movement, and taking them as seriously as cases of rape, molestation and pedophilia. *legal* auditory offensives will always remain a simple matter of opinion
.

text:
these past 5 months i have been working on myself and it has not been easy. though i wasn’t seeing the results that i wanted i kept going. .
.
today i got my first troll (hater). for the first time i felt strong and did not let it get to me as it use too. see i have been bullied. i have been back stabbed multiple time. i was sexually abuse for many years. i struggled with both depression and suicide.
.
. 
they don’t know that. however, what people think or say about me no longer define my feelings. i say yes to true freedom. though my healing has been a long journey, i am finally in a place where i can talk about it, with out feeling vulnerable.
so go and be yourself and find what makes you truly happy. i found mine ♥️😉
#metoo #survivor #transformation #healthjourney #talkaboutit #stopbullying

text:
most days my trauma doesn't rear it's ugly head; however, yesterday was an exception to that rule. i'm currently attending massage therapy school, and the therapeutic pose triggered me. for the rest of the day, i was an emotional mess. every time someone would ask me how i was, i cried. i felt ashamed that i allowed these feelings to come up and out. i said to myself, "i am stronger than this." later in the afternoon, i had significant lower back pain. my body's way of telling me that i needed to keep working on my sacral chakra. i needed to continue on this journey of releasing emotions built up inside and cutting those energy cords from the people who had hurt me.

i'm sharing this with you because we all are on a healing journey. while my pain might not be your pain, we still have our issues to heal. there might be days that you think everything is perfect and other days where it comes out of nowhere and grabs you only to make you fall in a heap of tears on the floor. these moments are there to show you that you can't let your guard down nor stop self-care. there will be moments that trigger past hurt and pain, but acknowledging them and taking the time to work through them is critical. no longer running from what is hurting you or causing you to suffer.

after allowing myself to release through crying, drumming, and writing a letter with the beautiful full moon, i feel much better. and next time i know i won't be so harsh on myself and will love myself through it. 💓🦋
name: Prana Mind-Body Healing

text:
as the tedx centennial college license holder, it is with outmost delight and pride that we wrap this evening with all the empowering talks on resilience from our brilliant speakers.

huge thank you to melissa grelo for being our mc for #tedxcentennialcollegetoronto - your bold and daring journey of career shifting is an inspiration to all those stuck in their current unfulfilling jobs -- seek what sets your soul on fire!

our panel of 13 speakers, covered war and refugee in afghanistan, being smuggled into canada and going from homeless to nurse, sexual assault, power abuse, refugee camps and leaving marriages, agriculture and future of a greener tomorrow, the illusion of magic and perception, the future of robots, humans and the 3 p's, identity and birth of a fusion cuisine and plenty of more enriching talks.

thank you to all the speakers for creating a rich environment for our audience and community at large; and a huge thank you to the hardworking, dedicated and passionate team that made tedx come true. thank you for your nights and days spent without sleep and for your tenacity in bringing this to our college.

resilience remains in the form of our conduct, our tenacity and drive amidst the pinning pain and heavy sighs of wars and missiles, heartache and treachery, disappointments and setbacks.

resilience is the tongue of our fallen shoulders and bloodied roads.

and amidst the fall remain standing tall and proud, remain humble and down to earth, for we have journeyed not in the footsteps of others. hurry not to label and taint someone - be kind, mindful and compassionate.

as the tedx ccto license holder, my takeaway is every single one of you and more. 
#tedx #tedxccto #resilience 
@tedx_official @tedxtoronto

our panel of 13 speakers, covered war and refugee in afghanistan, being smuggled into canada and going from homeless to nurse, sexual assault, power abuse, refugee camps and leaving marriages, agriculture and future of a greener tomorrow, the illusion of magic and perception, the future of robots, humans and the 3 p's, identity and bih of a fusion cuisine and plenty of more enriching talks.

thank you to all the speakers for creating a rich environment for our audience and community at large; and a huge thank you to the hardworking, dedicated and passionate team that made tedx come true. thank you for your nights and days spent without sleep and for your tenacity in bringing this to our college.

resilience remains in the form of our conduct, our tenacity and drive amidst the pinning pain and heavy sighs of wars and missiles, heaache and treachery, disappointments and setbacks.

resilience is the tongue of our fallen shoulders and bloodied roads.

and amidst the fall remain standing tall and proud, remain humble and down to eah, for we have journeyed not in the footsteps of others. hurry not to label and taint someone - be kind, mindful and compassionate.

as the tedx ccto license holder, my takeaway is every single one of you and more.

text:
anxiety is a powerful emotion. some of us use it as an advantage, but for the many, myself included at times, it is a crippling fear that stops you dead in your tracks.

of recent times i’ve learnt that this emotion and the reactions that come from anxiety, are all apart of a source of energy in your body waiting to be used. when we feel the wave of anxiety come over us, it is because we are entering into a moment that is unknown to us and our head brain does not like the unknown.

our head works in a two dimensional manner, yes no, right wrong, good bad, and if we are entering into a moment that is unknown, we immediately go to what is dangerous in that setting. this is when anxiety kicks in as the head brain runs through all of the scenarios of how you can be in danger.

it’s not your heads fault, because this is exactly how we have evolved over thousands of years, looking for the danger points at any given time, so we can out smart them. in today’s world though, we don’t have prehistoric animals trying to eat us, so we create our own creatures in our head to be in danger from. it is in our evolutionary make up, so it’s not your fault, it’s an inherent default position we go into when we feel the unknown is around us.

over the years my anxiety has been a crippling emotion, especially in my late teens into my early twenties. i made myself extremely sick to the point doctors thought i may have thyroid cancer. i kept looking for help because something in me said they’re not right. i saw my naturopath in the end and it was my head. i had been entering into some major unknown events in my life and my anxiety took a hold of me.

recognising anxiety is another source of energy i try to look at every moment with what can i bring to this and what can i receive from it. it takes the power of the head and where are the danger points away. and as much as you can, enter into each moment with love, see everyone as equal to you and you to them. we are all anxious human beings, it’s apart of our genetic make up, so don’t feel alone in this, because i understand and i am here with you. #compassion #understanding #love #mentalhealth #notalone #together #metoo

over the years my anxiety has been a crippling emotion, especially in my late teens into my early twenties. i made myself extremely sick to the point doctors thought i may have thyroid cancer. i kept looking for help because something in me said they’re not right. i saw my naturopath in the end and it was my head. i had been entering into some major unknown events in my life and my anxiety took a hold of me.

recognising anxiety is another source of energy i try to look at every moment with what can i bring to this and what can i receive from it. it takes the power of the head and where are the danger points away. and as much as you can, enter into each moment with love, see everyone as equal to you and you to them. we are all anxious human beings, it’s apa of our genetic make up, so don’t feel alone in this, because i understand and i am here with you.

text:
🏫 school photo c.1967 🏫
sunday, age 9
•
this was the year an anonymous report had been filed. it was the year that while the children were alone, a social worker stopped by. it was the *only* year a social worker paid a visit. that visit was the only time. her big sister was brave, told the woman they weren’t okay. and she left them there anyway.
•
this is my last october #tbt & i’m so glad to have been able to share these photos with you.🤗my heart is full having been able to pass all the wonderful responses along to the real-life sunday minor throughout her birthday month.🕯💗it’s made my favorite month of the year that much more special.🍂✨
•
one last sunday minor surprise to round out the month tomorrow (related to book fest📚) *and* a bit about why i pretty much ghosted you this week...
👻
•
anyone else having a week, too?😅
•

text:
so... megan kelly gets fired and her *lawyer* calls *ronan farrow*? ok, america is really reaching
.

and listen, this is *one* reason i don't want to file against random house as much as i *fucking hate* racist ass avery books -- there is absolutely no growth in shaming people, like... none at all
.

the goal isn't to actually stun-gun people into morality, but *teach them a lesson*, which is why i offered several times to *talk* to meg newman and lauren. i don't want them to be fired, i want them to learn *restraint*. there is no reason for me to know your a racist. you inherited my book when my original editor was fired, but as said, your a racist so you played me, throughout it all i remained unbothered, bc that's typical white girl behavior, and it was only when you rejected my book that i was like, "see, now; you fucked up; only irresponsible fuck off allow their personal politics to render their jobs un-doable". the fact that she is a cunt doesn't actually matter either, bc i treated her with the respect her position warrented ...bc i'm a good ass, responsible employee
.

see, meg newman runs a racist imprint. no black authors have been published on her health imprint on *years*, and black people suffer a disproportionately high mortality rate. you're telling me *nobody* thought to write about it but me? yes, they did, but she's a racist. so, she didn't make it past my junkyard of an instagram page, which made her think i was disposable... bc she is a racist
.

turns out my *entire family runs media*. know who was the first person called after the sony leaks? my dad. want to know who was in the sony leaks? my uncle. so, im very slow to pull the trigger bc in order for meg newman to keep her job in 2018 she has to prove that she's not a racist, so instead of apologizing shell just double down
.

i hate that shit; i have to mentally prepare for it. i kind of feel like i have to also say, "nobody get fired" bc that's white peoples answer to everything, and it solves nothing. lauren is an ambitious kid, this was meg fault, but she should keep feeding her kids ...spam and other foods racists eat
.

text:
female chefs aggressively on fire and inspired!

my biggest challenge was not being heard or getting the same opportunity or seeing people who looked like me. i was often the only woman, woman of color, african american woman. we have to stick together and bring women along,  share resources and access. @mstanyaholland

growing up, kitchens had a double standard. men who throw pans are seen as strong great leaders. as a woman you need to come out as a firecracker but when i talked straight i was fired for being bitchy and bossy. the only thing you can do is be better than them, to be focused, to prove you can do better than anyone else. being fired was the best thing that could happen to me. representation is important - as a woman and an immigrant. looking at me, now young women can see it's possible. its ok to be out here. it's ok to share emotions. it's ok to speak out. @chfshirleychung

there were no hr departments, no regulations. the new boundaries are that you don't touch women, don't speak in a vulgar way, to treat women as equals - or superior. i think men will be happy with this change as well because its a healthy culture where you can do better work. i curate my content and seize every opportunity to lift up women - that is what heartens me. @tablehopper

the point is learning, whether working for a man or a woman. @sweetdanib

i'm often up against gender standards even with men who work for me. some say it's not personal - but it is about relationships. i want my restaurants to be led by women, because they are marginalized and have the answers. i want to inspire without being tokenized. be collaborative not competitive. food spaces are a place for healing. @reem.assil

i'm a chef now - i don't follow rules. i'm not your friend or your mom. i'm a dona - i'm your boss. @dominicarice

#goodreads women exploring #diversity through food #bepeculiar

@illgrabmyown @mstanyaholland @chfshirleychung @tablehopper @sweetdanib @reem.assil @reemscalifornia @dominicarice @macys #culinarycouncil #metoo
